title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine flour and dry yeast in a bowl.
Mix honey in warm water and gradually add to dry ingredients.
Store in earthenware pot at room temperature for 2 days to 1 week.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crust from loaf bread and lay in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brown and drain sausage and sprinkle over bread.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and shredded cheese.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour tubular or angel cake type pan.
Combine eggs and sugar in mixing bowl and mix at high speed with electric mixer for 20 minutes.
Fold in flour. (Sprinkle small amounts of flour at a time with flour sifter and fold in.)
Put batter into greased pan and bake for 50 minutes. When cake is cooled, remove from pan and cut into 3 layers.
Set aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini, tomatoes and onions.
Grate cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, make 2 layers of the zucchini, tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Cover top with slices of uncooked bacon.

title: broccoli-cheese chicken
directions: Cook chicken in skillet with margarine until browned on both sides.
Stir in soup and milk and let come to boil.
Add broccoli. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt butter.
Add to scalded milk.
Add sugar and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, potatoes, yeast mixture and flour.
You have added almost enough flour when mixture is hard to stir and you have to turn out on board to knead.
These may be stored in refrigerator for future use.
Let dough rise to double in bulk.
Roll, cut out and place in still warm place.
Let rise to double in bulk again.
Bake at 400° until brown.
These are not as light as some rolls, but have a very good taste.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Add cake mix 1/3 at a time and mix well.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.

title: swirl pound cake
directions: Combine together first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat well with mixer.
Remove two 1-cup portions of batter in separate cups.
Mix cocoa in one cup and red food coloring in the other.
Pour all yellow batter in greased and floured tube pan; add remaining cups of batter, one at a time. Swirl batter gently with a knife.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Chop ham into small pieces (best if chopped with a chopper or food processor). Mix all ingredients except parsley in a large bowl until well blended. Divide mixture in half and form into balls. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: edible aquarium
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin; dissolve completely.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups ice and water. Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.

Remove any unmelted ice. If mixture is still thin, refrigerate until slightly thickened. Pour thickened gelatin into 4 dessert dishes. Suspend gummy fish in gelatin. Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into large casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Sprinkle cheese over top and melt.

title: salmon salad
directions: Flake the salmon.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients; chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza dough
directions: Put dry yeast in water to dissolve.
Put all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add water and mix with hands until it turns to dough.
Let rise, then punch down and let rise again.
Form into balls and use or freeze.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour; stir in cheese, mustard and red pepper.
Add milk; stir with fork until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork until mixed.
Turn dough out onto cloth; knead just until smooth.
Roll out.
Cut out and place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and soda.
Melt butter.
Add cocoa and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix by hand.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: mcnamara's irish potatoes
directions: Blend all ingredients together by hand to form a large ball. Pinch off small pieces and roll into small balls.
Coat with cinnamon. Allow to dry several hours before covering with plastic wrap.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Drain clams, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Set aside.
In medium skillet, cook onion and garlic in hot oil for about 4 minutes or until onions are tender.
Carefully add the reserved clam liquid, wine, basil or oregano and red pepper.
Bring the mixture to a boil and boil gently for 4 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add clams.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, toss pasta and clam mixture until well coated.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk with eggs.
Stir egg mixture into dry ingredients, mixing only enough to moisten. Stir in melted margarine, then orange rind and coconut.
Turn batter into well-greased muffin pans, filling only 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Combine syrup, fruit juice and ginger ale in a punch bowl.
Add ice cubes. Drop sherbet by spoonfuls.
Yields 50 servings.

title: mom's cherry almond cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and blend.
Add cherries, extract and nuts if desired.
Shape into balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Let cauliflower stand in cold salt water 1 hour.
Put into kettle with 3 quarts cold water and 1 tsp. salt; bring to a boil and boil 25 minutes or until done.
Be careful to keep head whole. Take out carefully and drain.
In sauce pan melt butter; add flour and milk.
Cook until it thickens; then add salt.
Put cauliflower in shallow baking dish and pour the white sauce over it.
Sprinkle cheese over top and a dash of cayenne pepper.
Put in oven and brown cheese.
Serve at once.
Note:
Can substitute asparagus for cauliflower.
Cost, including gas heat, = $0.1780 in 1917 terms.
From Telegram Conservation Cook Book.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: In a large bowl cream together the butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Stir together oats, flour and baking soda.
Stir into creamed mixture until blended.
Set aside.

title: barbecue salmon
directions: Combine cider and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Add butter and garlic.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until liquid thickens enough to coat the back of a spoon, about 20 minutes.
Remove marinade from heat and cool.
Pat salmon fillets dry and place skin side down on a rack.
Brush salmon with marinade evenly and let stand 20 minutes at room temperature.

title: yam pie
directions: Drain 1/2 cup syrup from the can of whole yams.
Put yams in circle slices; mix cornstarch with yam syrup, lemon juice and peanut butter.
Put a layer of yams on bottom.
Pour on half the liquid mixture, then repeat.
Cover with pie crust and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook noodles and drain. In saucepan, heat together soup, milk, onion, Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Stir well.
In casserole, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 ham and 1/2 cheese; repeat.
Melt butter in skillet and mix in bread crumbs; sprinkle buttered crumbs over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly and top turns brown.
Serves 4.

title: fig and pecan cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl, one at a time.
Add the pecans last.
In a buttered tube pan, cook for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: smutt peach pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; cook 1 minute.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature until slightly thickened, but not firm.
If it sets up, carefully reheat.

title: fresh apple cookie
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in salt, soda, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Mix well and add raisins, apples and nutmeats.
Bake at 400° for approximately 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Crumble bacon, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings; set aside. Mix cornflake crumbs with drippings.
In medium bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except bacon and crumbs.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch casserole dish, greased.
Sprinkle with bacon and crumbs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: "best ever" meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine all ingredients. Form into loaf. Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Drain off fat. Top with additional catsup and bake another 5 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray large baking dish with cooking oil.
Place rice on bottom, next place chicken on rice.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup, water and butter.
Bake 1 hour at 400°, covered, with tinfoil.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve when cheese has melted.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using a glass dish).
In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press firmly on bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: laurie's chicken fajita marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding oil last.
Pour over boneless, skinless chicken breasts in glass dish and marinate in refrigerator (covered) for several hours.
Grill chicken on barbecue grill, basting with marinade occasionally.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix asparagus, cream of mushroom soup, milk and half can of onions.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; heat until brown.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sliced, fresh strawberries.
Place sliced bananas over berries.
Mix pudding as directed on package; pour over fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, adding chunks of onion.
Add mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Season to taste.
Simmer gently for 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: fudge
directions: On medium-high heat, melt caramels, milk and sugar until caramels are completely melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Dump in chocolate chips and stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Stir in nuts and pour into buttered pan.
When it cools enough, refrigerate until firm enough to cut in pieces.

title: basil-cheese-tomato bread
directions: Spread butter over bread.
Sprinkle garlic powder over butter. Place basil over butter and garlic.
Add chopped tomatoes, then top with cheese.
Broil or bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: hot meat dip
directions: Brown beef, onion and green chilies; drain well.
Add sauce and cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with taco chips.
This is pretty warm, so you might want to use just one can of chilies.
Good for dips at parties.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Combine buttermilk, shortening and yeast mixture.
Add flour and sugar.
Stir until flour is moist.
Roll, cut and bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
Or place batter in greased bowl, cover and store in refrigerator.
Take out amount as needed.

title: crabmeat bites
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, blending well.
Chill.
Spread split muffins with cheese mixture.	Cut each muffin half into quarters.
Serve cold or slip under broiler until cheese is bubbly. Yields 4 dozen bites.

title: wine soup
directions: Bring the wine, water and spices to boiling.
Strain.
Discard spices.
Beat egg yolks with sugar until thick.
Slowly add the hot wine mixture, beating constantly until a thick foam forms at the top.
Be careful not to curdle the yolks by pouring hot wine too fast.
Serve in cups with wafers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sister barbara's fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine pecans, cherries, pineapple, dates and raisins with 1/4 cup flour.
Mix to coat.
Set aside.
Mix margarine, sugar, eggs, milk, flour, soda, grape juice, cloves, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix together,
Add fruit mixture
Drop by teaspoonful into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and food coloring.
Sift together flour, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately with buttermilk after each addition.
On medium speed, add vanilla.
Mix baking soda and vinegar and add to batter without beating; mix by hand. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.
Frost with whipped cream frosting.

title: fat man salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: dutch crepes(pancakes)
directions: Mix together to a flowing consistency.
Using an 8-inch frypan lightly oiled, pour in 3 ounces and fry both sides to golden brown.

title: oriental salad
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce.
Cook in microwave.
Cool and cut into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl, break apart noodles; set aside flavor packet.
Place sesame seeds and almonds on cookie sheet; toast in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Let cool, then add to noodles.
Add cabbage, onions and broccoli; toss.
In small bowl, combine flavor packet, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix and pour over noodles.
Add chicken and mix.
Marinate overnight or several hours.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix in order given and shape in a small roll.
Wrap in wax paper and put in icebox overnight until firm.
Cut in small slices and bake in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: sausage macaroni bake (for a crowd)
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, brown sausage in skillet; drain well and set aside. Melt butter or margarine in large pan.
Add carrots and celery; cook about 10 minutes, or until almost tender, but not brown. Blend together flour, onion, mustard and salt.
Stir into vegetable mixture to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix with macaroni and browned sausage until well blended.
Portion into 2 lightly buttered 20 x 12 x 2-inch pans.
Sprinkle tops with potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 48 servings.

title: spice tea
directions: Pour boiling water over the tea, cloves, orange rind and cinnamon.
Cover and steep for 3 to 8 minutes.
Stir.
Strain through fine strainer.
Serve hot with cinnamon sticks or peppermint sticks in each cup.
Serves 8.

title: taco casserole dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add taco mix and salsa; simmer.
Smooth cream cheese on bottom and sides of pie dish and pour in beef mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
(May add lettuce, tomato, sour cream, black olives, etc.
for variety.)

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes as directed on box. Place butter, caramels and milk in top of a double boiler; stir until caramels are melted.
Cool slightly; spread over baked cake.
Spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain juices from oranges and pineapple; add water to make 1 c.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add to jello, which has been dissolved in hot water.
Add all ingredients except cream.
Let chill until thickened before adding whipping cream.
1 envelope of plain gelatin can be added to hot jello to ensure it will be firm enough.

title: cream corn
directions: Crush crackers and corn flakes.
Mix with corn, onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Fill blender 3/4 full with ice cubes.
Add the lemonade, vodka, water and strawberries. Blend on high speed until nice and frothy.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, 1 egg and 2 tablespoons lemon flavoring into a dough.
Spread in greased pan.

title: aunt grace's banana pudding
directions: Place vanilla wafers in pan.
Mix mashed bananas, milk, and flour to thicken.
Boil till thick.
Pour over wafers.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and
cook cake as directed on box.
While hot, poke holes in
top
of
cake.
Pour
Eagle
Brand milk and cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool, top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon and pour into pan.
Pour box dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Pat nuts onto cake mix.
Spoon melted and cooled margarine over nuts evenly.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. When cooled, invert cake on platter and peel off wax paper.
Mix frosting.

title: sugar-free banana cream pie
directions: Cut bananas into thick slices about 1/4-inch each. Evenly cover the bottom and lower edges of the pie crust with banana slices. Beat together milk and pudding mix for 1 to 2 minutes. Gently pour pudding over the banana layer and refrigerate.
Allow 1 hour to set.

title: rave review cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: banana muffins
directions: Puree bananas in blender (1 cup).
In medium bowl, combine bananas, eggs, sugar and butter until blended.
Stir in vanilla. In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Stir banana mixture into flour mixture until evenly moistened.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, flour and salt. Place the blackberries in pastry shell. Spread sour cream mixture on top of pie. Combine bread crumbs, remaining sugar and butter or margarine and sprinkle on top of pie. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Serve warm.

title: supper salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Mix together the salt, mayonnaise and pepper.
If you like, add 1 teaspoon grated onion to this mixture.
Add chicken, Swiss cheese, pickle and hot rice.
It is important that the rice be hot.
Add peas; mix gently.
Cover and chill about 1 hour, or for a very different flavor, serve at room temperature.
Serve on salad greens garnished with tomatoes and olive wedges.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: banana spice cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Lemon Butter Icing.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water.
Cook until clear. Let cool.
Add sliced strawberries.
Let set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter a large casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onion in dish.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Put chops on top of potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix can of tomato soup and 1/3 soup can of water together and pour over chops.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix well.
Place small pieces of raw bacon over top.
Cover. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover, bake 45 minutes more. Serves 12.

title: crusty pepperoni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent dough in one piece onto ungreased baking sheet.
Brush pepperoni with egg yolk and roll in flour.
Place on dough and roll up, covering completely.
Tuck in ends neatly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice thinly and serve with your favorite mustard for dipping.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Microwave for 25 to 35 minutes on Medium-High, or until well done in center.
Pour off liquid and let stand, covered with foil, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: three layer irish potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake layers at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tests done.

title: sausage-ham dressing
directions: Steam vegetables in 1/4 cup Mazola margarine until tender. Mix vegetables with bread crumbs, sausage and ham.
Moisten thoroughly with turkey stock (or canned broth or cubes).
Season to taste.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can serve with gravy made with stock or broth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli.
Mix dressing with melted margarine.
Stir 1/2 of dressing mix into broccoli mixture and pour into a casserole dish. Top with remainder of dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-yogurt pie
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Beat in yogurt and honey; chill until partially set (mixture will be the consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Whip gelatin with electric mixer until light and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes.
Reserve a few whole berries for garnish; slice remainder and fold into gelatin.
Chill again, if necessary, until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Turn into crust.
Chill until firm, several hours or overnight.
Garnish with whipped cream and reserved berries.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Season to taste.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes; mixture will be soupy.
Cook 1 package noodles and put in casserole.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Pour over noodles. Put meat on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet & sour sauce
directions: Combine above ingredients together in a sauce pan.
Heat over low heat stirring with a whisk often until jelly is melted.
Brush on chicken, ribs, or pork chops.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cocoa.
Gradually add water; bring to a boil.
Add milk and boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts. Serve over ice cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions; bake in 2 layers.
When cool, split layers.
Make filling.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Mix well and chill thoroughly.
Reserve 1 cup filling mixture.
Spread the rest between layers of the cake as you stack layers.
Mix reserved 1 cup filling with Cool whip.
Ice top and sides of cake.
Seal in an airtight container.
Refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: stay up all night coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Place rolls on top of nuts, sprinkle dry pudding mix on top of rolls.
Melt butter in small skillet and add in sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls.
Fix night before and leave in oven overnight.
Next morning remove from oven and gently press rolls that have risen out of pan back.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take top rack out of oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour until stiff.
Add margarine, milk, coconut and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust.

title: cream cheese cheese ball
directions: Blend together both packages of cream cheese.
Add beef, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use three heaping teaspoonfuls for mug size; add boiling water.

title: super tasty celery dish
directions: In saucepan, combine celery, water, water chestnuts and salt. Simmer 8 minutes; drain.
Place vegetables in mixing bowl.
Add soup, oleo, bouillon granules and pimiento; mix well.
Place mixture in 1 1/2 quart casserole (greased).

title: banana split pie
directions: Layer sliced banana on bottom of crust.
Mix pudding mix with milk for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add drained pineapple to pudding mix. Pour pudding and pineapple mixture over banana layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, add eggs and blend in the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add flavorings and bake in greased tube pan (10-inches) at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing cake.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and mix well.
Sift flour with soda, mix flour and sour cream alternately.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake for 1-1/2 hours in a 350 degree oven.
Do not open oven door while baking.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar; let rise. Mix egg, sugar, vegetable oil, salt and 1 cup warm water to yeast mixture.
Add about 4 cups flour.
Put in a greased bowl and let rise.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.

title: poppy seed finger sandwiches
directions: Cook onion in margarine until clear.
Mix margarine and onion with Worcestershire, poppy seed and mustard.
Using a sharp knife, cut dinner rolls without separating them down the middle.
Spread margarine mixture over dinner rolls on both cut sides.
Layer ham and cheese over bottom half of dinner rolls.
Replace the tops. Heat at 350° for 15 to 20
minutes.
Cut sandwiches apart into 48 finger sandwiches.

title: scramble party mix
directions: In a large pan, melt butter and add all liquids and seasonings.
Add cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Bake at 225° for two hours, mixing every 20 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: date nut cake
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water and pour over dates.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add chopped nuts to cake mixture.
Make a stiff batter. Pour in loaf pan and bake in slow oven at 300° to 350°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces; brown in skillet 2 minutes.
Add bouillon, garlic, soy sauce and salt.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Stir in pepper and onion; cook an additional 2 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cake flour.
Drain cherries, saving juice. Combine sugar, cake flour and salt.
Gradually stir in juice.
Add almond extract and lemon juice.
Combine with cherries and pour into pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter and put top crust in place. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.
(This recipe is for the 1 pound size can.)

title: crispy bacon shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl except bacon.
Cover. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain shrimp from marinade, saving liquid.
Wrap each shrimp in 1/2 slice bacon.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Cook marinade down to 1 cup liquid.
Put in a cup. Serve surrounding liquid with toothpicks for dunking.
Serves 6. An excellent appetizer or hors d'oeuvre.

title: chicken breast and linguine in white wine sauce
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; add crushed garlic and saute until soft.
Add onion and bell pepper (red and green); saute until soft.
Add chicken breasts and saute over medium-high heat until almost done, about fifteen minutes.
Add white wine, Italian seasoning, lemon juice and parsley flakes; cover and continue to heat over medium to low heat until chicken is done.
Add cream; cover and continue to heat.
(Linguine should be almost ready to serve.)
If needed, mix cornstarch in about 1 1/2 tablespoons water and stir into sauce for thickening.
It should not be too thick, but the consistency of a creamy sauce.
Remove chicken and place on a plate.
Pour sauce over drained linguine in a pot or bowl and mix.
Serve linguine on the side.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
A nice green salad with Italian dressing and garlic bread or sticks, served with a chilled white wine will top off a great meal.
Try spumoni for dessert.
Make it a perfect evening; put on an Italian opera or a great Italian singer on the tape deck or CD player.
If it's a really romantic evening, set the table with red and white linen, candles and dim the lights.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Heat the 3 cans of soup; add cheese and milk to desired thickness.
Cook broccoli until about done.
Put cooked rice in roaster.
Add heated soups and broccoli; top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are slightly browned.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Place the cranberries, sugar, water and orange juice in a heavy saucepan; bring to the boil, stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Reduce heat and simmer until the berries break open and the liquid is reduced a bit. Remove from the heat; add cinnamon and orange zest. The sauce will thicken as it cools. It will last refrigerated up to a month. Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: pasatelli soup
directions: Mix all together well.
If mixture is sticky, add more bread crumbs.
Put through meat grinder and break into 2 or 3-inch lengths.
Boil in 1 quart chicken broth.

title: helen's nut roll
directions: Mix together all ingredients, folding in the egg whites.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Cream butter or margarine with sugar.
Blend in egg, milk and flavorings.
Blend into dry ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator overnight or for 2 hours.
Roll chilled dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes with floured cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar together until sugar dissolves. Pour over cucumbers, onions and green peppers.
Cover.
Let stand overnight.

title: chili willie soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in the hot water.
Put everything together in large pan.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot fruit juice; mash in cream cheese.
Stir in fruit.
Add nuts and Coca-Cola.
Chill until firm.

title: walnut buttered brussels sprouts
directions: Remove wilted leaves of Brussels sprouts; trim ends of stems and make shallow cross cut in each stem.
In large pan, bring sprouts and water to boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.

title: shrimp and artichoke casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt 4 1/2 tablespoons butter and stir in flour.
When blended, gradually stir in milk and cream, stirring constantly, with a wire whisk.
When the mixture is thickened and smooth, season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Add chicken, celery, onion and seasoning to stock.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cover and cook until noodles are almost tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Mix flour with small amount of milk until smooth.
Add remaining milk.
Stir into soup.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: "america samo's" fresh tomato salsa
directions: Tomatoes can be seeded and chopped.
Mix all ingredients. Makes about 3 1/2 cups of salsa.

title: apache dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for bread.
Hollow out each loaf.
Spoon filling into bread bowl.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve with crackers or more bread for dipping.

title: bachelor brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
In same pan add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and cocoa and mix well.
Pour in greased and floured sheet pan or sprayed with PAM.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes. (No more no less.)

title: anginetti cream puffs
directions: Drain pineapple, leaving a little juice.
Soften cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Add whipped topping.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple.
Blend all 3 ingredients for about 1 minute at low speed.
Slice off tops of anginetti.
Drop filling from tablespoon onto bottom layers.
Replace tops.
Refrigerate puffs until ready to serve.
Filling should be enough to fill 1 package of cookies.

title: potter's clay
directions: Blend flour and cornstarch with enough water to make a paste. Boil water and salt; add to cornstarch mixture.
Cook until clear. Cool overnight.
Add 6 to 8 cups of flour and knead until right consistency.

title: pasta and pepperoni salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta, according to directions.
Rinse under cold water and drain well.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir or toss well.
Chill and serve.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Make indentation in each with a thimble.
Fill with jam or jelly of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes or until very light brown.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in yeast and add shortening.
Mix thoroughly.
Put on floured bread board and knead until smooth.
Roll out as biscuits and cut.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake in 450° oven until done.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes 45 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in 3-quart baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brown flour potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes in water until done.
Melt the lard or butter in heavy frypan.
Add the flour; stir over medium heat until flour is brown.
Stir into potatoes and water; cook for a few minutes.
Add milk to make soup of desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan or baking dish, layer the potatoes and onion.
Crumble beef over onion.
Spread the soups over the beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with chips.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until meat is no longer pink.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and cover.
Place in fridge overnight before serving to fully blend flavors.
Keeps in fridge up to a week.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: butterscotch bubble bread
directions: Grease an angel food pan or Bundt pan. Drop frozen rolls in. Combine pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts in a small bowl. Sprinkle over rolls (It will sift down as it rises).
Cut butter into patties and arrange over top.
Cover with foil (Just lay on top, shiny side up; do not seal).
Let stand overnight on countertop.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in a bit of olive oil.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer, covered, for about 20 minutes or until eggplant is softened.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake until knife comes out clean at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with sugar and egg yolk until smooth.

title: corned beef ribbons
directions: Mix corned beef spread, pickle, horseradish and sour cream in medium size bowl.
Spread evenly on 24 slices of bread, leaving remaining 12 slices unspread.
Make 12 sticks of 2 spread slices (spread side up) and 1 unspread slice each.
Wrap in plastic bags or wax paper.
Refrigerator overnight or until serving time.

title: (700 watt) microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Pack mixture into 2 quart microwave dish.
Make a round hole in the middle of meat so that meat cooks evenly. Cover with wax paper and cook in microwave oven 5 minutes at medium high.
Rotate dish one 1/2 turn and cook on high for 15 minutes or until done.
Top with 1/2 cup of ketchup mixed with 1/2 tsp. mustard.
Allow to sit for 5 - 10 minutes before serving. This can also be cooked in conventional oven.
Just don't cover with wax paper.

title: crock-pot spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef well in skillet and place in crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients, except dry spaghetti; stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (on high for 3 1/2 hours).
Turn to high for the last hour and stir in dry spaghetti.

title: baked chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a pan.
Melt butter and pour over chicken. Then add a dash of pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mexican quickie
directions: Cook ground meat and drain.
Add chopped onions and cook until clear.
Add picante sauce, chili beans, water and black olives and heat until hot.
Serve over rice.
This is great with green salad and steamed tortillas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lakin's smurf cooler
directions: Add ingredients together in glass.
Add ice and top with cherries, if desired.

title: best ever pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and water to boil until syrup.
Cube or slice pickles.
Put back in jar in layers.
One layer of pickles, next garlic clove, another layer of pickles, then garlic until you have them all covered.
Pour on syrup.
Put in refrigerator. Ready to eat in 2 days.
Will keep for some time.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Saute onion, carrots, celery, basil and parsley in 1 Tbsp. butter until tender.
Add broth, potatoes and beef.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Meanwhile, in a small skillet, melt remaining butter.
Add flour.
Cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes until bubbly. Add to soup.
Bring soup to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream.
Serves 8 (2 1/4 qt.).

title: microwave chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine morsels in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High (100% Power) for 3 to 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Store in airtight container. Yields about 4 dozen clusters.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add water and vinegar. Cook gently until thick and clear (10 to 15 minutes). Stir in margarine and salt. Add beets; reheat and serve.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease bottom of 10 x 15 x 1 jelly roll pan and place wax paper over bottom of pan. Grease (Pam). Combine ingredients. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle confectioners sugar on no lint towel. Dump cake onto towel and remove wax paper. Roll lengthwise in towel and let cool.

title: fried green tomatoes(1930)
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Get oil pretty hot.
Flour, salt and pepper the tomatoes to taste.
Put in skillet.
Cook until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham, bread crumbs and pork together.
Mix all ingredients, mixing in about 1/2 cup of milk or enough to make moist.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350°.

title: cranberry candles
directions: Heat cranberry sauce and strain.
Mix liquid, boiling water and gelatin, stirring until completely dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt and mix well.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened. Add mayonnaise and beat with rotary beater until fluffy.
Fold in reserved cranberries, apples and nuts.
Stir and chill until slightly thickened.
Fill cranberry sauce can 3/4 full of mixture for the largest candle.
Spoon remaining mixture into assorted sizes of glasses or cans.
Chill until firm.
Unmold candles onto serving tray and insert birthday candle halves into the center of each "candle."
Make the day before serving.

title: coffee punch
directions: Dissolve coffee in water and chill.
Add sugar and milk.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into punch bowl and spoon in ice cream, stirring until partly melted.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 30 to 35 people.

title: meatball soup
directions: Mix ground beef with rice, egg, tomato sauce, salt, cumin and chopped onion.
In a pot put 2 quarts of water with 2 tablespoons salt to a boil.
While water boils, make small size, or as decided, meatballs.
Add meatballs to boiling water one by one until all meatballs are added to boiling water.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve with cabbage; cut in fine pieces and lemon.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well.
Pour in pie crust and chill 4 hours.
When ready to serve, top with strawberries or blueberries, if desired.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: picante sauce (salsa)
directions: Squeeze juice out of tomatoes.
Save juice.
Grind up everything and put in kettle.
Add the salt, sugar and vinegar. Dilute 1/2 cup cornstarch in tomato juice to make a gravy.
Add when boiling.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Open kettle.
Fill jars and seal.
Makes about 7 to 8 pints.

title: oriental casserole
directions: In skillet, cook beef, celery, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain.
Add 1 cup water; bring to boiling. Combine the cornstarch, sugar and ginger.
Blend in the soy sauce and 2 tablespoons water.
Add to beef mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the drained chop suey vegetables.
Break apart the frozen peas and add to beef mixture.
Cool quickly.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Knead. Roll out, cut and let rise for 5 minutes.
Bake at 475° until brown.
Dough will keep in a well covered container for a week.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix
together ingredients, add the water last.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, almonds, mayonnaise, salt, onion and lemon juice.
Put in a greased casserole.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: over 65 cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Let cool.
Poke holes in top of cake.
Pour pineapple mixture over top of cake. Let stand 15 minutes.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Spread over top of pineapple mix.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut in squares.
Center with dab of Cool Whip.
Keeps 5 days.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Split Twinkies into 1/2 longways.
Lay on their sides with the filling up.
Pour fruit cocktail (juice and all) over Twinkies. Layer with sliced bananas.
Layer with pudding (fix the pudding as per package directions).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs until creamy.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon, mixing well.
Then stir in remaining ingredients. Mix together and pour into 1 bundt pan, 2 small loaf pans or 1 large loaf pan.
Bake for 70 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma kellie's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Next, add apples (peeled and diced) to mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to apple mixture. Next, add vanilla and chopped nuts (optional).
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Enjoy!

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate at least 2 hours (preferably overnight) to bring out all of the flavors.
Also delicious on turkey and roast beef sandwiches.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Saut first 6 ingredients for 15 minutes. Add 2/3 of cheese to meat mixture; stir until cheese melts. Add 8 ounces tomato sauce and mushrooms; mix well. Stir in macaroni and mix again. Top with 8 ounces tomato sauce and sprinkle with rest of cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together in bowl, sugar and flour.
Melt together oleo, cocoa and hot water.
Pour melted mixture over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. During the last few minutes, mix your icing to pour over the hot cake.

title: hearty italian bean soup
directions: Take approximately 1 1/2 cups of the white kidney beans and mash them until smooth in a medium bowl.
In a 5-quart saucepan, cook the ham, celery, carrots, onion, zucchini, basil and pepper in hot oil until the vegetables are tender and begin to brown (about 15 minutes).
Stir in the stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, chopped spinach, mashed white beans and 2 cups of water, using a spoon to break up the tomatoes.
Over high heat, bring to boiling. Reduce the heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 minutes to blend the flavors.
Stir in the remaining beans; heat through.

title: grandma's cheddar-crust apple pie
directions: Mix 2 1/4 cups flour, salt and cheese.
Cut shortening and 1/2 cup margarine into flour mixture.
Sprinkle 4 to 6 tablespoons cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until it forms a ball.
Shape into two balls.
Flatten one and wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Roll out other ball and place in pie plate; cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well. Add banana.
Add rest of dry ingredients, then cinnamon to taste. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook hen until tender; salt and pepper.
When done, take off the bone.
Use a 9 x 12-inch pan or dish to cook it in.
Use a cup of hot broth and mix enough flour to make the dough real stiff.
Then take half of the dough and roll out on a cloth or what you use to do that and let it be rolled out real thin and cut into strips.

Then take half of the chicken and broth and put it on the dish, then put half of the pastry on that, then the rest of chicken and broth, then put the rest of the pastry on that and place in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
You can use a fryer, also.
Let it brown on top good.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat in confectioners sugar.

title: real old-fashioned lemonade
directions: In a large pitcher, combine lemon juice and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine ground beef, rice, onion, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into 6 round patties.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each patty.
Fasten with a wooden toothpick.
Place in an ungreased, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or to desired doneness.

title: cinnamon apple tortilla cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small cup combine 2 teaspoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Lightly spray tortillas on both sides with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle both sides with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Press each tortilla into a muffin or custard cup, forming a cup.
Bake tortilla cups 5 to 7 minutes just until edges begin to brown.
Cool completely on rack.
Press to open while tortillas are still warm, if necessary to maintain cup shape.
Squeeze excess moisture from grated apple.
Place in medium bowl.
Stir in yogurt, nutmeg, the remaining 2 teaspoons of sugar and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: quick and easy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large pot over medium heat, melt butter. Cook onion and celery in butter until just tender, about 5 minutes. Pour in chicken broth. Stir in chicken, noodles, carrots, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink and soup is hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 6 minutes or until tender; drain in colander. In a 2-quart casserole over medium heat, cook onion and garlic until tender in margarine.
Stir in soup and seasoning.
Add cheeses, stirring until melted.
Stir in sour cream, broccoli and cooked noodles.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: party chicken or chicken supreme *
directions: Wrap each breast in strip of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Mix undiluted soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake, uncovered, in very low (275°) oven for 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: huckle buckle coffee cake
directions: Cream 1/4 cup butter and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Add egg and mix.
Add milk and blend well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick pan coating.
Spread dough in pan.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter to form coarse crumbs and sprinkle on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. **

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out insides, leaving a thin shell.
Mix and mash potatoes with butter or margarine and salt.
Gradually add soup and chives. Beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon into shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) at 450°
for 15 minutes, or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and curry powder; bring to a boil. Drain fruit and arrange in a shallow pan.
Pour hot sauce over it. Garnish with cherries.
Bake at 325° until it bubbles (25 to 30 minutes).

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add brown sugar. Boil over low heat about 2 minutes. Add milk; continue stirring. When mixture comes to a boil, add confectioners sugar. Can be mixed with electric mixer until thick enough to spread.

title: charlotte's chicken rotel spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, pepper, and olives in oleo.
Add soup, Rotel, Velveeta, and chicken.
Mix with vermicelli.
Bake in large casserole dish (I spray mine with Pam to ensure it's easier to clean) at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: cheesy zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter.
Cook until just tender. Mix eggs and cheese.
Combine with the zucchini and onion.
Add spices and mix.

title: hungarian style goulash
directions: In Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook onions, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Add stew meat, paprika, salt and bay leaf.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 3 hours or until meat is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf, stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese peanut bread
directions: Dissolve
yeast in lukewarm water.
Heat cottage cheese until lukewarm.
Stir
in
honey,
salt, soda, eggs, yeast and nuts. Gradually
add
flour.
Place in greased bowl; let rise until double.
Punch
down;
divide
dough into 2 equal parts. Place in two greased loaf pans and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can make into rolls.

title: ray's carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs and oil in small bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Add egg mixture; mix well.
Stir in carrots and pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa; set aside.
Cream together 1 1/2 cups sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 3 tablespoons sugar (optional), chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: soy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
Layer in casserole and top each layer with cottage cheese.
Cover with white sauce, top with Melba toast crumbs or soy grits and bake 30 minutes in moderate oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on side panel. While noodles are cooking, beat yolk lightly with fork and add cream. Melt butter in a saute pan. Add cream and egg mixture to melted butter. Simmer slowly. When noodles are done, drain and put in a large bowl. Pour cream over noodles and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Toss until noodles are well covered. Add remainder of the cheese and toss.
Serve immediately.
You can also add ham.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda and dry yeast.
In saucepan, beat cottage cheese, water and butter until mixture is warm.
Add egg and warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at lowest speed until moistened. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese; simmer.

title: ground beef goulash
directions: Place ground beef in a 2-quart ovenware casserole.
Cover. Cook in microwave about 7 to 8 minutes.
During cooking, stir twice to break up meat.
Combine water, tomato sauce, soup mix and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over dish halfway around after 5 minutes. After 10 minutes, stir.
Cook another 5 to 6 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Total cooking time: 20 minutes.
Recipe yields: 4 to 6 servings.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Heat over medium heat to near boiling. Add cake mix and nuts.
Pour into a 13 x
9-inch pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: tutti fruiti surprises
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar. Stir in melted shortening.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in nuts, dates and fruit.
Spread in a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake until top has dull crust. Cut into squares while warm; cool and then remove from pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear. Add strawberry Jell-O. Cool. Pour on fresh strawberries. Pour into cooked pie crust. Chill.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish. Spread sausage, then the cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over casserole and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, water, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Also this dough can be wrapped around chocolate mint wafers and topped with walnuts. (Not with white cream center.)

title: fried shrimp
directions: Remove head and shell from shrimp but leave fantail.
Split shrimp down back and remove vein.

title: holiday aroma
directions: Mix ingredients in crock-pot and add water to fill container. Bring to a boil and then simmer for as long as you desire.
This mixture will last about one week.
If you wish to use it again, strain out spices and add fresh juice and water.
Be sure to re-use your spices in the next brew, maybe adding a little more. Do not drink!

title: meat loaf soupreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: chess  pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add well-beaten egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in unbaked crust rather slowly like a custard pie.
A little flour dusted over crust will help to prevent its soaking.

title: vermont apple pie
directions: Core and pare apples.
Slice thin.
Spread about half the slices in a pastry shell.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except maple syrup.
Mix well. Spread half of this mixture over apples.
Add rest of apple slices and spread remaining crumb mixture evenly over top.
Bake in moderate 350° oven about 50 minutes.
Heat syrup to boil.
Pour over pie.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Roll into cigar shapes, size of crackers.
Roll in paprika; wrap in foil.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: hamburger delicious
directions: Cook and drain seashells.
Brown the hamburger with celery and onions.
Combine mixture with soups.
Pour into large greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Pour juice and olives into casserole and stir lightly.
Return to oven for additional 10 minutes.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, water and vanilla in a heavy skillet. Stir constantly until it turns dark in color.
Pour into buttered pan.
Place Hershey bars on top.
Spread chocolate around with spatula.
Top with sprinkled chopped nuts.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in a cool place.

title: cornell formula chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat together egg and oil and add balance of ingredients. Place chicken on grill and baste with sauce.
Turn frequently and baste each time.
Keep flame low by having a squirt bottle handy.

title: mama's old-fashioned black walnut caramel cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, flour, milk and eggs together.
May need a small amount more milk.
Add black walnut flavoring.
Spray cake pans with Pam or grease and dust with flour.
Pour batter into pan and bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: cajun cornbread skillet
directions: Heat oven to 400°. In 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet, cook onion, pepper and sausage in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil until vegetables are tender.

title: mango papaya smoothies
directions: In a blender, blend the mango, the papaya, the yoghurt, the lime juice, the honey, the almond extract and 1 cup ice in batches until the mixture is smooth.
Blend in an additional 1/2 cup ice if desired to thin the smoothie mixture to desired consistency. Divide the mixture between 4 large chilled glasses and decorate each with a lime slice.
Serves 4.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together. Melt butter in iron skillet.

Add sugar mixture and mix lightly. Combine beaten egg yolks and milk. Add to mixture, stirring constantly. Cook slowly until thick. Add vanilla and blend well. Pour in pie shell. Cover with meringue. Brown in oven. If you don't like meringue, you can use whipped topping.

title: meat ball sauce
directions: Mix together jelly and chili sauce.
Cook meat balls in separate pan.
When done, put in pan with sauce and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add cream, then flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla; mix all together. Drop by tablespoons on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: morning brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, stir together the pancake or waffle mix, cocoa and sugar.
Combine milk, oil and egg and add to bowl, mixing just until blended.
Stir in bran flakes.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until the top springs back when lightly pressed. Cut into squares, top with vanilla yogurt or fresh fruit, if desired.

title: light pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and put in 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: bing cherry pie
directions: Line large pie plate with whole vanilla wafers.
Stir Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice in mixing bowl until thickened.
Add Cool Whip.
Add cherries which have been drained of all liquid. Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into pie plate lined with wafers. Chill in refrigerator at least 2 to 3 hours before serving or overnight.
Cool Whip holds up better and longer than whipping cream.

title: potato bacon soup
directions: Fry bacon, until crisp, in a 3-quart pan.
Add onion and saute two or three minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add potatoes and water and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
Stir in soup, sour cream, salt and parsley.
Gradually add milk.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
Yields 7 cups.

title: peggy's homemade chili
directions: Saute ground beef, celery, onion and pepper for 10 minutes. Add other ingredients and cook on low for at least 2 hours.
For a larger crowd, I double the recipe and sometimes triple.

title: orange-apricot jello salad
directions: Mix and simmer in saucepan:
Jell-O, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat in cream cheese, apricot baby food and Cool Whip.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear up angel food cake.
Mix sour cream, milk, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; whip until blended.
Toss cake in cream mixture. Layer cake, pie filling, cake and pie filling.
Looks nice in a large brandy snifter or large glass bowl.

title: ham and swiss pockets
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon a portion on 1 crescent.
Bring corners to center top and seal edges.
Moisten corners, if needed.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed tenderloin
directions: Saute onion over medium heat until tender.
Add spinach, salt and pepper; saute until spinach wilts.
Stir in cheese and tomatoes.
Cut tenderloin lengthwise down center.
(Do not cut completely through to the bottom.)
Lay flat and spoon spinach mixture down center of tenderloin.
Secure with string. Tenderloin won't close completely.
Place cut side up in a pan/casserole dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes(quick and easy)
directions: Peel potatoes if tough skin, otherwise scrub and rinse.
Cut into thin slices but not all the way through (use spoon handle to prevent cutting through).
Put potatoes in baking dish, fan them slightly.
Drizzle with butter, sprinkle herbs and salt.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned and cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix first eight ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook until well blended and thickened.
Place carrots, onion and pepper rings in large bowl.
Pour sauce on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will stay fresh for several days.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: skippy burgers
directions: Make ground beef into 4 patties (not too thick) and fry. Split buns and toast.
Shred lettuce.
Slice tomato and onion. Slice pickle longwise into thin slices.
Spread mayonnaise on buns. Top with meat, lettuce, tomato, onion and pickle and serve.

title: belvidere casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in oven uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook pared squash and onion together in enough water to cover for 8 to 15 minutes.
When tender, drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish for 1 hour at 300°.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: *I usually partially cook these 3 ingredients first.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix apples, apple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Place in pie tin containing unbaked pie crust.
Sugar Twin may be added to apple juice if a sweeter filling is desired. Mix flour, oleo and Sugar Twin together and crumble over sliced apple mixture.
Instead of crumb crust, a regular top crust may be used.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven fried taters
directions: Slice potatoes in fourths, lengthwise.
In a plastic bag, mix ingredients.
Add potatoes; shake until coated.
Bake in oven at 375° on lightly greased cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes.
Rotate potatoes.

title: pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Then add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well and then add pumpkin.
Add all the dry ingredients together.
Then add to the first mixture.
Pour batter into two well oiled bread pans.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: six bean chili with sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Add celery and onions; simmer until well done. Add sugar, tomato paste, chili powder and dry mustard.
Mix well. Put contents into crock-pot.
Add all canned products (beans and vegetables).
Stir in molasses.
Cook 5 hours or more on high or 7 hours on low.
Serve with French bread and salad.

title: joey's chocolate hi ho's
directions: Put peanut butter between two crackers.
Melt chocolate bark in saucepan and dip the crackers and peanut butter sandwich into the mixture.
Then put them on wax paper and let them dry.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon or mackerel, pepper, egg and flour in a large bowl. Spoon into hot grease and fry until golden brown.
Serve immediately with rich and brown gravy.

title: creamy salad dressing(for potato salad)
directions: Place sugar, vinegar and water in saucepan and bring to boil. Combine egg, milk-cream mixture, mustard, cornstarch and salt. Add to hot mixture; cook 5 minutes or until thickened.
Cool and use for potato salad.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth and melted.
Pour over cornflakes and stir until cornflakes are well coated.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Break in small pieces when cool.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in Bundt pan or any pan with a tube in middle.

title: floy's hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and 2 teaspoons sugar together and let stand 1 hour.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar, Crisco, egg and salt until light.
Add yeast mixture and 2 cups warm water.
Add flour to make not too stiff dough.
Let raise until double.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Place in pan and let raise until double.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together yogurt and Cool Whip and pour into pie shell. Place into freezer.
A quick dessert to have on hand if company should drop by.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugars and cooking oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix. Add the dry ingredients.
Mix; add water last.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Remove
from
oven;
poke
holes at once down through
the
cake
to the pan with a round handle of a wooden spoon.
Only
after
poking
holes,
combine
pudding mix with sugar
in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk, add butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Quickly pour hot pudding evenly over warm cake; into holes to make
the stripes and over the top to "frost" the cake.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar in warm water.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Stir in warm milk, 2/3 cup sugar, shortening or butter, salt, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Saute almonds in a little water and sugar until dissolved and candied (stir so they do not burn).
Tear lettuce in bowl, add vegetables and oranges on top.

title: herbed beef and vegetable stew
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Coat meat, shaking off excess.
Heat oil in a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat until it looks thin and rippling but not smoking.
Brown beef in 2 or 3 batches. Return all meat to pot.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, wine, garlic, herbs, pepper and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Add carrots, potatoes, green beans and celery.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes longer, stirring once or twice, until meat and vegetables are tender.
Garnish with herbs.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast (makes a sticky dough).
Roll out on floured surface and cut in rounds.
Place on greased pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: jennie's chicken supreme
directions: Line lightly greased baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap bacon strips around chicken breasts and place on beef.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Mix sour cream and soups together.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Mix and cook until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water. Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop on waxed paper.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place on cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: Press rolls in jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate cake(fat-free)
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, combine honey, applesauce, eggs, vanilla and water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in a greased and floured sheet cake pan.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Rub with garlic and thyme.
Brown in hot oil in nonstick skillet.
Combine juice and cornstarch and add to meat. Combine honey and mustard and remaining juice.
Add to meat and add pineapple.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens.

title: apple jelly cookies
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls size of a walnut.
Flatten out and make dent in center with thumb.
Fill with apple jelly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (color will be light brown).
Let cool. Remove from pan.

title: slumgolien
directions: Cook 1 cup elbow macaroni.
While that cooks, brown ground meat and drain.
In large pot, place ground meat and cook onion in ground meat until transparent.
Add green pepper, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mixed vegetables.
When cooking, make sure it is on simmer and stir often.
Add macaroni when finished and drained.
Stir until well mixed and add salt and pepper. Serve hot with fresh loaf of bread and salad.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with mixer.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add melted butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Wash, stem and slice okra.
In a large pan, saute okra in drippings. Add green pepper, onion, garlic, tomatoes, paste, water and seasoning.
Simmer about 20 minutes, then add shrimp and sausage or ham. Cook 45 minutes.
If bacon is being used, add after 35 minutes. Serve over fluffy rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cinnamon toast originals(8 to 10 children)
directions: Let children cut bread slices into shapes with cookie cutters. Brown the bread in broiler or oven.
With pastry brushes, have children brush each shape with melted butter.
Immediately shake on sugar and cinnamon.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Add sauce, spices and cottage cheese. Layer 1/2 of noodles in 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with 1/2 of sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Repeat with remainder.
Bake covered in foil on 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato sour cream casserole
directions: Place in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bavarian meatballs
directions: Beat egg; add milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Add onion and ground beef; mix gently, until ingredients are just combined.
Shape into 2-inch meatballs.
Brown slowly in oil in a large skillet.
Drain excess fat from pan.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat inside of a 9 x 9-inch square baking pan with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper in a bowl. Stir in cornmeal and cheese. Beat egg slightly in a small bowl. Stir in milk, oil and corn. Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until blended.
Pour batter into pan. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes until top is golden brown and springs back when gently pressed with a finger.
Cool on wire rack. Cut into squares to serve.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake as per directions on package.
Divide batter into two 9 x 13-inch pans (greased and floured).
I use an 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, bring to boil 1 cup milk and 1 cup sugar.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add coconut.
Pour over hot cake.
Heat to rapid boil 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup milk and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Pour over hot cake.
Cover with almonds.
I usually mix 1 cup chopped almonds into the chocolate mix.
Can toast almonds also.

title: aunt mabel's casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in a little oil, then add ground beef and brown.
Chop Spanish olives and add, then add 1 can tomato soup and 1 teaspoon allspice.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except crumbs and margarine. Pour into a baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs which have been mixed with margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: stir 'n roll baking powder biscuits
directions: Measure oil and milk in same cup together, but do not mix.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg and beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture on slow speed and mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until they begin to brown.

title: dilly green beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Fill jars as tightly as possible.
In each jar place red pepper, mustard seed, dill seed and clove. Make syrup.

title: chicken breasts(up to 16)
directions: Place chicken in dish.
Mix sour cream, soup, mushroom soup, mushrooms and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered, at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, 1/2 cup whole milk, 1/2 cup evaporated milk, eggs and vanilla.
When smooth, add bread cubes and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Stir in raisins, if desired.
Pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle top with nutmeg or cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan make 2 to 3 layers of tortillas, chicken, onion and green chilies.
Over each layer pour soup with milk. Top this with cheese.
Bake at 300° for one hour.
I cover mine with foil.
This keeps the cheese from drying out before all is done.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars.
Add small amount of milk to chopped candy and melt in microwave.
Add sugar, eggs, evaporated milk, Eagle Brand milk and whipping cream.
Mix together and pour into electric freezer.
Fill freezer with milk (2% or whole).
Freeze as your freezer instructs.

title: carbonara sauce
directions: Combine butter and milk. Add other ingredients. Mix.
Serve over pasta.

title: special occasion chicken
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Add mushrooms and shallots. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cook 10 minutes or until tender.

title: snow peas with sesame
directions: Place snow peas and carrots in a strainer.
Set the strainer in the sink.
Pour boiling water over vegetables for about 1 minute, then pat dry.
Place vegetables in a medium size bowl and stir in orange rind, oil and seed.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine pudding and milk; beat with electric mixer until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Gradually blend in chocolate until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Turn into crust and freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and raspberries, if desired.
Prep time:
15 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour
cream,
Velveeta
cheese, onions and salt together.
Place in
greased
baking
dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and then sprinkle crushed corn flakes on cheese.
Pour melted butter
over
corn flakes.
Bake about one hour at 350°.

title: rosemary's salmon pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together except dill.
Put in containers and sprinkle with dill.
Keep refrigerated and use within a week. This freezes well and is best served with "Wheat Thins."
Great with wine!

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add the strawberry Jell-O and mix well.
When it begins to set in refrigerator, pour it over sliced berries that have been arranged in a pre-baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, fry onion in a tablespoon of butter.
Add chicken.
Cook until brown.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: You will also need copper wire and 1/8 to 1/4-inch satin ribbon

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvers
directions: Split muffins and spread with mixture of all ingredients. Bake in 375° oven until golden.
Cut into wedges and serve.
May be frozen flat on a pan, then stored in plastic bag.
Keep frozen until needed.
To use, remove and place on pan and broil until crisp.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles
directions: Boil mixture if desired or mix all together and pour in cold. Keeps in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomatoes and green onions in a big bowl.
Cover with cheese.
Brown hamburger in skillet; season with taco sauce. Pour over cheese.
Cover with Fritos.
Serve with your favorite salad dressing.

title: kiwi's no bake cookies
directions: Blend sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Heat and stir mixture over medium flame until well blended, then raise to boiling point for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and uncooked oats.
Beat until blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper. Let the cookies cool and enjoy!

title: zucchini dessert squares
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly, reserve 3 cups.
Pat remaining crumb mixture into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain excess fat, if any.
Chop onion and add to hamburger.
