Cook over medium heat until onion is done.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Mix together; add chili powder, garlic powder, cumin, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer on low heat for several hours.
Stir occasionally.
You may add 2 cans of kidney beans the last hour, if desired.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ingredients while slow boiling the head of cabbage.
Cut and peel away whole leaves and drain on paper towels.
Stuff and roll with edges down.
Place in baking dish or oven pan.
Cover with second can of tomato sauce.
Pour about 3/4 c. of water around edges of pan.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend cheese and enough cherry juice until bright pink.
Whip cream and blend into cheese.
Mix.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Rinse lima beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and add 3 1/2 quarts boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly until beans are tender and soup has thickened.
Serve as main dish with crusty bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and beaten eggs.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Place in a buttered casserole and top with a thin layer of cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Can add grated cheese (Cheddar or Velveeta) with the bread crumbs.

title: green garden salad
directions: Make salad dressing using lemon juice, oils, seasonings and garlic.
Shake well to mix.
Wash and dry lettuce; break into bite size pieces.
Roll in damp paper towels and refrigerate until serving time.

title: grated raw sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add milk and melted oleo. Add vanilla, salt and sweet potatoes.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup. In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, 1 cup margarine and salt.
Blend well.
Press in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly-roll pan or two 9-inch square pans.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
In a small saucepan, combine corn syrup, 2 tablespoons margarine, water and butterscotch chips.
Boil two minutes, stirring constantly. Sprinkle nuts over partially baked crust.
Pour cooked mixture over nuts.
Return to oven and bake an additional 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into 48 bars.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until set.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix the sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing
well after each addition.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and
chopped
nuts.
Mix	the
vanilla wafers. Place in a glass serving bowl.

title: cold parsleyed ham
directions: Trim any fat from ham and dice.
Combine with stock, wine, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer gently for 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving the stock and place ham in a wet glass bowl that you've dusted with a little finely chopped parsley.
Soften gelatin in a little water.
Stir into hot stock and add remaining parsley and vinegar. Allow to cool until syrupy.
Pour over ham.
Fluid should cover meat.
Allow to set for 12 hours before unmolding.
Slice for 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves or 1 tube pan.
Tastes better if allowed to stand overnight before slicing.
Can freeze too.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse.
Add other ingredients, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Saute margarine, cheese whiz, soup, onions and celery.
Cook Broccoli and add to sauteed items.
Add rice.
Put into greased 9 inch square dish.
Bake at 350°to 375° for about 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup plus a little milk

title: baked white fish
directions: Place fish in baking dish and spread soup and sour cream over the top of the fish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, depending on the thickness of the fish.
(It may not take quite an hour.)

title: toasted coconut goodies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Cream well. Add 1/2 cup shredded coconut and chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoon of mixture into remaining coconut and form into 1-inch ball until it holds its shape.
Repeat until entire mixture is used.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Cool.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Cook the margarine,
brown
sugar
and Karo syrup for 4 minutes.
Add the baking soda and salt.
Pour over the popcorn and put in a 200° oven for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Grease and flour pans. Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and mashed bananas. Sift together the dry ingredients and combine with the liquid mixture. Do not overmix. Pour into 2 bread loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool and remove from pans.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Place peeled potatoes in a glass baking dish.
Mix Italian salad dressing with melted butter.
Pour over potatoes and coat well.
Bake at 300°, covered, until done.
May be browned under broiler for roasted taste.

title: golden punch
directions: Bring 2 cups water, cloves and sugar to boil to dissolve sugar; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cinnamon stick; cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook bouillon cubes, water, onion, potatoes, celery and carrots for 20 minutes in a large pot.
Add package of frozen mixed vegetables.
Mix the soup with 1 can of water.
Add to pot. Add the cubed cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Be careful; soup burns easily.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add flour, salt, shortening, eggs and water.
Make dough into a soft ball.
Roll out on a floured surface; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cut into small squares; put in chicken broth.
Cook until tender.

title: yogurt-cucumber vegetable dip(lo-cal)
directions: Press cucumber with paper towels to remove as much moisture as possible.
Combine cucumber and onion in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with cucumber.
Blend thoroughly. Cover and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Best when used within 1 week.
Makes 1 1/2 cups, or 24 tablespoons.
Calories per 1 tablespoon: 8.

title: yummy good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, combine raisins, Eagle Brand milk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and set aside.

title: whole wheat chocolate cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients except water.
Then add hot water. Bake in	a
12-inch Dutch oven for 1 hour with 12 coals on top and 7 coals on the bottom.

title: spanish hot dog sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a nonstick skillet and stir until meat is fine.
Cook on low heat until onions are cooked through.
Boil hot dogs; put on a bun.
Cover with sauce.
Can put melted cheese on top, too.
This can be used on nacho chips, too, with melted cheese.

title: 3-cup cake
directions: Pour all in a mixing bowl; beat on high speed until batter is smooth.
Pour into iron skillet that has been greased with margarine and floured.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen edges; turn out on plate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, 1 stick margarine and 2 cups powdered sugar; beat for 15 minutes, no less!
Pour over graham cracker crumbs, then slice bananas over this.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread prepared Dream Whip over this.
Sprinkle sliced cherries and nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight or place in freezer for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Let this stand for 12 hours in covered bowl in refrigerator before serving.
This will keep for better than 3 weeks.

title: my favorite meatloaf
directions: By hand combine all ingredients.
Then put in a large rectangle baking pan.
Pat flat.
Bake at 375 for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Drain grease off.
Then mix 3/4 c. brown sugar and enough salsa to glaze.
Pour over meat and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until glaze starts to get gummy.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and cut out mushroom stems.
Saute stems in butter with finely chopped onions.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Stuff in mushroom cups and bake in a buttered pan 15 minutes at 350°.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons water.
Add 1 cup boiling water; set aside to cool.
Combine pineapple, sugar, salt, lemon juice and cherries.
Add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Let partially congeal and fold in one container of Cool Whip.
Rub brown off cake and break in bite size pieces.
Put a layer of congealed mixture in bowl and then a layer of cake pieces, alternating layers and making sure to begin and end with congealed mixture.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Top with the other container of Cool Whip.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: pat's chocolate balls
directions: Mix sugar, cracker crumbs, peanut butter, coconut and vanilla. Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Mix well.
Form mixture into small balls.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Place popped corn in large brown paper bag.
Put brown sugar, oleo, Karo and salt in a 2-quart dish.
Stir and boil in microwave 2 minutes on High.
Put in 1/2 teaspoon soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn in sack.
Close sack and shake well.
Cook bag and contents on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and cook 1 minute more on High. Spread on a cookie sheet.

title: hot artichoke heart dip
directions: Finely chop artichoke hearts; mash with fork in bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients (except paprika) and combine well.
Spread in a pie pan or flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).
Good with Triscuits.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix all and pour over baked mixture. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Blend thoroughly in large mixing bowl.
Put in 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with 1 can French fried onions.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Over all, pour 2 cups water.
Blend with a fork.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal with egg and buttermilk.
Put oil in skillet and put in oven until oil is hot.
Remove from the oven and pour about 2 tablespoons of oil in cornbread mixture.
Pour into skillet and bake at 450° until brown.

title: fast beef stir-fry
directions: In large frying pan, melt margarine.
Add garlic, onions and peppers.
Cook until onions are beginning to become tender.
Add beef, lemon juice and pepper mixture.
Cover and cook until beef is done.
Cook 2 cups of Minute rice according to directions.
Serve vegetables and meat over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Wash, pare and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip slices into mixture of egg, salt and pepper.
Coat with cracker crumbs. Cook in skillet for 15 minutes until crisp and brown, turning several times.

title: fettucine primavera
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook broccoli, zucchini, green pepper, onion and basil in butter until vegetables are tender. Stir in tomatoes and mushrooms.
Toss vegetable mixture with hot fettucine.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 5.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thick strips; dust with flour and pepper.
In large skillet, brown meat in margarine or butter.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth or cubes. Cover and cook about 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream; cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle. Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Turn under edge; flute.

title: pineapple ring
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Add enough water to remaining juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Add to dissolved jello.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts (horseradish, if desired).
Spray a 6-cup mold with Pam and pour in.
Chill several hours; unmold onto serving dish.

title: cheese dip
directions: Sprinkle crab meat over cream cheese and then pour cocktail sauce over
crab meat and cheese. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: candy fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt the chocolate and add oil.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon on waxed paper.
Let set until cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball and roll in the chopped pecans to coat.
Serve with vanilla wafers.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese; mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend zucchini.
Add nuts, raisins and fruit just long enough to chop.
Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased deep muffin cups (3/4 full).
Bake at 425° until golden brown 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 5 to 9 popovers.

title: basic chili
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add onions and garlic. Cook until onions are transparent.
Add herbs, salt, tomatoes, sauce and chili powder.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Blend flour and water and add to mixture.
Stir well and cook 20 minutes.
Add beans and seasonings.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling
water
over
dates.
When cool, add soda. Mix sugar, oleo, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add
date mixture and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious cheese dip
directions: Blend all together well, using mixer.
Serve with potato chips and all kinds of snack crackers, etc.
A family favorite!

title: western sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, oil and buttermilk; gradually stir in dry ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Knead and form biscuits.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: ground beef and tater casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add beans, soup, mushrooms and seasonings. Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes and half of the onions.
Spoon potatoes around edge.
Bake at 350° for	25 minutes.
Top
potatoes
with
cheese
and	remaining onions. Bake
minutes
longer
or
until cheese is melted. Serves 4 generously.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Mix the sugar with 1/4 cup water (or a little more). Cook on low heat until it spins a thread.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fluffy.
Pour syrup over egg whites in a thin stream, beating all the time. Beat until cool. Add the vanilla and cream of tartar (optional).

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs with a fork; mash the bananas.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla.
Add this to the eggs and shortening mixture.
Add the dry ingredients and chopped nuts.
Pour the batter into muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise. Fold in broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until top is browned.
Makes 6 or 8 servings. Chopped onion or a can of drained, sliced water chestnuts may also be added.

title: orange chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter until browned.
Set chicken aside. In skillet, add flour, orange juice concentrate, bouillon, water and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil; add chicken and cook five minutes.
Put on platter; add oranges and green onions.
Serve with rice.

title: bread and pizza dough
directions: Mix salt and sugar together in the water.
Add yeast and dissolve completely.
Pour flour in a large mixing bowl and slowly add water while beating on medium speed.
When the dough is completely mixed, place on a floured surface and hand knead thoroughly.
Oil the mixing bowl and put the dough back in to rise.
Cover with plastic wrap and a towel.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain; melt butter and add flour.
Stir until smooth; gradually add milk and cheese.
Stir until melted; add noodles, salt and next 3 ingredients.
Pour in casserole.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: homemade dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and add eggs, salt, pepper, sage, poultry seasoning, croutons and chicken broth.
Then add celery and onion. Bake at 325° until done.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients, except zucchini, in bowl.
Add zucchini last.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry candies
directions: Combine milk, coconut, 1 package gelatin, almonds, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Shape mixture into strawberries.
Roll candies in remaining gelatin, coating thoroughly.
Let candies dry until firm.
Make leaves with icing on top of candies.
Store in a covered container.
Yield:
4 dozen.
Keeps well.
Will last for at least a month if stored in airtight container.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and salt and form into 1-inch balls; brown (either in broiler or on top of stove).
On top of stove, add cranberry sauce and cook until the sauce melts.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cook and simmer 20 minutes or until meatballs are done.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with noodles (I have used as toothpick finger food).

title: mexican fiesta pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in chili powder.
Add cream cheese, chilies, olives and eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Sprinkle with cornmeal. Spoon meat mixture over batter to within 1/2-inch of outer edge of pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Continue baking 5 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and mayonnaise.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Roll dough into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Smash garlic to form paste with anchovies in wooden bowl.
Add dry mustard, 1/2 lemon without seeds and Worcestershire sauce.
Add coddled egg and beat with fork to form nice paste.
Add olive oil, vinegar and pepper.
In skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil and garlic.
Brown chicken strips and sprinkle with fried chicken seasoning.
Toss into salad.
Add cheese and croutons at last minute.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place over medium heat and bring to boiling point.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag and pack in jars.

title: best yet meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape in pan; top with ketchup, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: creole catfish
directions: Saute, in olive oil, green onion, onion, bell pepper, parsley, white wine and garlic for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes, V-8 juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, cayenne pepper and catfish. Simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: easy grilled rosemary chicken
directions: Put all ingredients (except garnish) in a 1-quart zipper type food storage bag.
Press out air.
Seal and turn to distribute dressing.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours or up to 24 hours, turning bag occasionally. Remove chicken and discard dressing.

title: spatzle soup
directions: Mix flour, egg and salt with enough cold water to make a very stiff batter; beat until smooth.
Drop batter by teaspoons into boiling water.
Boil until they rise to the top.
Drain.
Put in broth, celery and carrots.
Heat and serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add fruit cocktail (juice and fruit), vanilla and egg.
Mix and pour into greased pan.
Top with 1/2 cup of brown sugar and 1/2 cup of nuts.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: lemon lush cake
directions: Combine margarine, flour and walnuts.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Beat softened cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Make lemon pudding as directed on box.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip and finely chopped walnuts, cover and refrigerate.

title: vickie's apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oil, then add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Mix thoroughly by hand.
Batter will be thick.
Add apples.
Cook 1 hour at 350° in a sheet cake pan.
Glaze with powdered sugar and water, if desired.

title: made from scratch applesauce
directions: Wash apples and cut in half; remove stems and cores, but leaves skins intact.
Place in a large pot.
Add cinnamon, vanilla, lemon zest, juice, sugar, wine and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until apples are soft.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Remove and discard cinnamon stick and vanilla bean.
Puree apples and pan juices in a blender for a smoother sauce or process for a chunky texture.
Makes eight servings.

title: hot cross buns
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 1/2 cup flour. Warm milk and butter (120° to 130°).
At low speed, beat warm liquid into dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Beat in 1 egg and 1 cup flour to make thick batter; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in raisins and add enough flour (2 to 2 1/2 cups) to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead 10 minutes, adding more flour as needed.
Shape into ball; place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with bowl and let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Punch down; turn onto floured surface and divide into 15 pieces.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Shape into balls and place in pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut a cross on each bun; brush with remaining beaten egg.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 15 minutes.
Using icing of 3/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon milk to make cross on each bun.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt jello in 1 cup hot water. Stir well. Add 1 cup cold water. Stir well. Add pineapple with juice. Add cranberries and nuts. Pour into mold. Chill until set.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Peter Stuyuesant, Governor of New York, was organizer of the first volunteer firemen in America.
In 1648, he pushed through the first law regarding fire prevention.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling point in a saucepan.
Stir in all at once the cup of flour.
Stir constantly until mixture leaves the pan and forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat in one at a time the 4 eggs; beat until smooth and velvety.

title: thumbprint clues
directions: Put an oven rack in the center of the oven.
Preheat to 350°. Put butter and sugar in the mixer bowl and beat on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Scrape the sides of the bowl every once in a while.
Add the yolk and almond extract.
Mix on medium-high until yolk is completely blended.
Add half the flour at a time and mix on low speed after each addition.
Pinch off a small piece of dough about the size of a quarter.
Roll it into a ball and put on cookie sheet.
Lightly press your thumb in the center, leaving an indentation.
Shape the rest of the dough the same way, spacing the cookies about 1 inch apart.
Fill each indentation with about 1/2 teaspoon jam.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool completely before eating them.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Blend Cool Whip with cream cheese.
Add sugar and lemon juice until well blended.
Put in pie shell.
Top with pie filling. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: basic cake layers 1-2-3-4
directions: If using all-purpose flour, add 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix according to how ingredients are listed in the order they are.
Bake at 350° until done.
May take 1 hour or more.
Test with knife in center.

title: homemade shake and bake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Store in a covered jar.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Add water if too thick. Mix well together, cook for 30 minutes.

title: baked grits
directions: Stir grits and salt into briskly boiling water in heavy pot; return to boil, reduce heat and add butter.
Cook 2 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add 1 cup evaporated milk while stirring. Remove from heat and add 1 cup (or more) Mozzarella cheese, shredded, on top.
Put grits in preheated oven at 350° just long enough to melt cheese.
Remove from oven and let cool for a few minutes.
You may also want to add bacon bits.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and boiling water and place over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil until it will form a fine thread when dropped from a spoon.
Remove from the fire and pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture loses its gloss and becomes thick.
Add nuts, cherries, salt and vanilla.
Pour into slightly buttered pan.
When cool, cut. (Requires a long beating to thicken.)

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cover with water and soak overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and dry.
Put grape leaf in bottom of jar; add 3 heads of dill, garlic, red pepper and onions.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Bring vinegar, 3 pints of water and canning salt to a boil. Pour over cucumbers and seal.
Do not open for 6 weeks.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add pecans.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poor man's quiche
directions: Empty contents of Potatoes O'Brien with peppers and onions in an 11 x 7 x 15-inch pan.
Scramble six eggs in separate bowl; add 2 tablespoons milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tuna and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pan with nonstick cooking spray. In large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Cook until potatoes are tender (do not drain).
Mash the vegetables, leaving slightly lumpy.
Add butter, cheese, milk and bacon bits.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted and the ingredients are hot and mixed well.
Yields 8 to 9 cups.

title: apricot filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Keep adding flour and mix by hand until dough is right to roll out.
(Don't make too stiff.)
Cut cookie with round cookie cutter.
Put 1 teaspoon filling between each cookie and seal with a fork around edges. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: blueberry cake roll
directions: Grease an oblong pan (9 x 12-inch).
Mix first four ingredients and press dough into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; set aside.

title: artichoke and shrimp casserole
directions: Drain and slice artichokes and arrange in buttered baking dish.
Saute sliced mushrooms for about 6 minutes.
Add to baking dish.
Spread cooked shrimp over the mushroom and artichoke mixture.

title: easter bread
directions: Mix and let rise until doubled in bulk.
You may make loaves or twists or bread rings.
Let rise until doubled in bulk again, then bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add browned hamburger, flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Top with topping mixture below:

title: carrot ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat until thick.
Add carrots, water, lemon juice, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into carrot mixture. Generously oil a 3-quart ring mold; dust lightly with bread crumbs.
Turn mixture into mold.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven and allow to cool 3 minutes before loosening edges with dull-edge knife.
Turn onto heated round serving platter.
If serving to guests, put tiny green peas in center of ring and cauliflower florets around outside of ring.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: patty pans
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat butter until fluffy.
Beat in sugar gradually, until light, add eggs one at a time.
Combine cornstarch, flour and baking powder; add to mixture until well blended.
Spoon into small muffin tins.
In a preheated oven at 325° bake 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Store in sealed containers.
Yields approximately 36.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted oleo together and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip and milk together and beat until stiff.
Pour on cracker mixture.
Add Thank You cherries on top. Set in freezer until set.

title: orange milk shake
directions: Mix together in blender and serve.

title: slovakian nut candy
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat and stir sugar until melted and golden brown.
Stir in pecans, vanilla and salt.
Pour immediately onto buttered foil.
Roll quickly with buttered rolling pin to about an 8 x 8-inch square.
When completely cool, break into small pieces.

title: minute muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: rich muffins
directions: Combine eggs, milk and butter or shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture and stir only enough to moisten.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream sandwiches
directions: Bake your favorite chocolate chip cookie recipe.
Cut ice cream into 1/2-inch thick circles or squares the size of your cookies. Place ice cream slices between 2 cookies and enjoy.
Best when cookies are warm.

title: fresh strawberry pie(jackie brunson's)
directions: Wash, drain and stem strawberries.
Place the berries in the bottom of the baked pie shell. Slowly cook the sugar, cornstarch, water and salt until glossy.
Pour the hot mixture over the strawberries and place into the refrigerator until cold.
(May add a few drops of red food coloring.)
Just before serving, cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: sour cream filling
directions: Beat the egg. Add the sugar, flour and sour cream. Cook until thick. Cool and add the nuts.
Delicious between chocolate cake layers!

title: better than sex cake
directions: Blend together the first 6 ingredients.
Mix the last ingredients together and bake in a tube pan for 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.

title: doris' pecan brittle
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan with aluminum foil. Butter foil and set pan aside.
Combine pecan pieces, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook to hard crack stage (300°).
Stir in butter, vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture into prepared pan, spreading thinly.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.
Yield:
3/4 pound.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together the flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Set crust aside.

title: jumbles
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by the tablespoon and sprinkle with nutmeg or coconut.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 1 cup of nuts if desired.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Combine all ingredient into large pan.
Simmer until tender. Note:
May substitute potatoes with dumplings or wide noodles.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all 4 ingredients in an electric blender container; blend until very smooth.
Yields 1 1/4 cups or an amount equal to a 14 ounce can.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: fillet magnifique
directions: Place fish in single layer on heavy-duty aluminum foil large enough to fold and seal over all ingredients.
Melt butter and add rest of ingredients; blend well.
Spread over fish.
Fold and seal edges of foil tightly.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serve on heated platter. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Mix brownie mix with egg and water.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding with 2 cups milk, then fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Top with the rest of Cool Whip and break Heath bars up.
Top off with the candy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar, then Cool Whip. Pour into crust and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: saucy skillet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, peel them and slice them.
In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onions; cook 2 or 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes or until hot (do not boil). Sprinkle with parsley and bacon.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and baking soda, mixing well.
Set aside.
Beat orange juice, eggs, oil and orange peel until mixed thoroughly.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: picnic hamburgs
directions: Prepare hamburgs the day before a picnic, then heat and serve the next day.
Saute 1 tablespoon chopped onion and add to meat. Moisten bread in milk and add to meat.
Mix well and make into patties.
Saute sliced onion and remove from pan.
Fry hamburgs and remove from pan.
Add soups with 1 1/2 cans water and heat 5 minutes.
Into a slow cooker, add hamburgs, onions and soup alternately.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Next day, heat about 1 hour until hot.
Serve on hamburg rolls with sauce. Serves 10.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except pepperoni and onions.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle top with pepperoni and onions.
Bake 25 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all together. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Set aside.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks, add heavy cream and sugar and mix well.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Add chopped rhubarb to this mixture and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425 degrees in a preheated oven until rhubarb is tender and filling is set, approximately 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites and add brown sugar, pour over pie and return to the oven to bake until brown.

title: mocha cake
directions: In an 8x8-inch baking, mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.

title: "ho-ho cake"
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package
in
a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Use angel food cake pan (preferably).

title: marinated layered lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce in large bowl with lid.
Add in layers the celery, onion, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Cover with 1 cup of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.
Garnish with tomato, chopped eggs or bacon bits.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half the mixture over graham crackers, then place second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour remaining pudding over and top with more crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then frost with chocolate frosting.

title: special potatoes
directions: Wash potato.
Cut into slices (with skin on).
Add butter and potato slices to skillet.
Add onion, salt and pepper. Continuously stir and flip potatoes with spatula for about 5 minutes.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix jello, pecans, coconut, condensed milk and vanilla.
Shape mixture into strawberries.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Combine and mix well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. This makes almost a gallon before adding ginger ale.
This does better if mixed a day before and refrigerated.
This punch is yellow.
If you want pink or red, add red food coloring to get your desired color.

title: country casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer sliced onions and potatoes and sausage.
Pour corn on top.
Add soup and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice in a 6-quart pan.
Heat until cranberry sauce melts.
Make meatballs with remaining ingredients and cook in cranberry sauce mixture until meat is done.
(No need to brown meat first.)

title: city chicken
directions: Place veal cubes onto six (9-inch) wood skewers.
Combine cracker crumbs and next four ingredients.
Combine milk and egg. Dip meat in the egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In skillet, brown meat slowly on all sides in hot shortening.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup of boiling water and add to meat which has now been placed in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover, bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: holiday wreaths
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Add corn flakes cereal.
Stir until well coated. Portion warm corn flakes mixture, using 1/4 cup dry measure. Using buttered fingers, quickly shape into individual wreaths. Dot with red cinnamon candies.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add other ingredients and mix.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix in large pan, 13 x 13-inch.
Heat pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over warm cake.
Slice bananas over pineapple mixture (use 4, if small).
Prepare pudding according to directions and pour over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Mix coconut and pecans and sprinkle over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in a pan, then add the milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: emerald salad
directions: Melt Jell-O into 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Put mixture on low heat and add marshmallows, heat until dissolved.
Let cool.
When mixture begins to thicken remove and whip until it is smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped cream last.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook 3 hours on low heat; stir often.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix broth, butter, milk, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and lower heat. Then cut your dough into 1-inch squares and add to broth. Cook about 15 minutes. Do not stir. Add cut-up chicken. You may shake the pot to allow room for chicken.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake until golden brown; set aside to cool.

title: lemon-baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a casserole dish.
Combine oil, lemon juice, oregano or tarragon and garlic powder.
Brush on the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove cover and brush again with oil-lemon mixture.
Continue baking, uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: partridge casserole
directions: Parboil partridge breasts and legs with carrot and onion in water to cover for about 30 minutes.
Drain and take meat from bones.
Mix together meat, mushrooms, mushroom soup diluted with milk and noodles.
Adjust salt and pepper, if necessary.
Turn into well buttered casserole and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook on medium heat and stir until thick.

title: tome hot dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs; put a slice of cheese inside of sliced hot dogs.
Wrap with 2 slices of bacon; use toothpicks to hold together.
Put hot dogs in deep fryer 2 to 3 minutes.
Put hot dogs in a deep fryer 2 to 3 minutes.
Put hot dogs into warm hot dog rolls.
Top with mustard, onions and ketchup.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Dice unpeeled red potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes. Place in a large Dutch oven, cover with water and bring to a boil. Let boil for 10 minutes or until 3/4 cooked. In a separate large Dutch oven, combine melted margarine and flour, mixing until smooth. Place over low heat and gradually add milk, stirring constantly. Continue to stir until smooth and liquid begins to thicken. Add melted Velveeta; stir well. Drain potatoes and add to cream mixture. Stir in pepper and garlic powder. Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place soup into individual serving bowls and top with crumbled bacon, shredded cheese and chives.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of pie crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.
Stir pudding into milk in large saucepan. Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into crust.
Place plastic wrap on surface.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: banana yogurt graham snacks
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon on 1/2 graham cracker.
Top with thinly sliced banana and another graham cracker half.
Freeze.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Saute ground meat, onion and garlic together.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and tomato sauce in a round oiled casserole. Arrange in alternating layers the buttered tortillas, meat sauce, olives and cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Add 3/4 cup water over all.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Cut in pie shaped wedges.
Serves 6.

title: easy cranberry chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and soup mix together. Pour over chicken. Bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauerkraut casserole from netherlands
directions: Brown meat in small amount of fat, then add water, ginger and bay leaves.
Stew together.
Add potatoes and sauerkraut; cook until potatoes are soft (at least 1 hour to blend flavors).
The Dutch people simmer this dish for hours over low heat while they are busy working in the fields.
Reheating enhances the flavor.

title: mary's bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line bottom of greased 9 x 11-inch glass pudding dish with raisins.
Break up bread; put in dish.
Pour liquid ingredients over top of bread, making sure all the bread is covered.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Put in oven at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1/4 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar and dissolve 1 package of yeast in the mixture.
Blend 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup shortening.
Add 1 egg and beat.
Add 1 cup warm water and yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour (use mixer for mixing).
Let rise until double in size, punch down, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: For 8 smaller portions, cut each potato in half lengthwise. For 4 large portions,
cut a small slice off the top of each potato.
Scoop out middles, leaving a 1/4 inch shell.
In a large bowl, mix potato, salt, pepper, margarine, milk, green onions and 1/2 cup
of
the
cheese.
With
a large spoon, mix well, mashing potato
pieces as you stir.
Spoon equal amounts of potato mixture in
shells.
Top with the rest of the cheese and parsley.
Bake at 350°
for
10 minutes, or until stuffed potatoes are hot and cheese
is
melted.
You
can
also bake these in the microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: vanilla refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
(I use white Crisco because they hold their shape better.)
Gradually add sugar; continue creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and gradually add to mixture. Add nuts.
Mix well and shape into roll about 1 3/4 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice in 1/8-inch thick slices.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cooling rack.

title: mandarin salad(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Drain all fruit. Add coconut and marshmallows. Mix well.
Add sour cream and toss slightly. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: switchel
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir until sugar is dissolved. Chill or serve over ice.

title: chicken and crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion; saute about 10 minutes or until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add the stock and the cream slowly.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1/2 minute, stirring constantly.
Arrange chicken, peas and crab meat in layers in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with sauce.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes or until browned on top.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Drain eggplant and add other ingredients.
Put in baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done, when knife comes back clean.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt with enough water to be manageable.
Food coloring can be added.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Lightly grease a large casserole dish with margarine or butter.
Spread 2/3 of the crushed Doritos over bottom of dish. Layer chicken over chips and then add green chilies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all but cheese; add to broccoli and pour in casserole.
Cover with cheese and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Cut ends from zucchini, then cut in lengthwise slices, then cut slices in half and in thirds (crosswise).
Place cut side down in hot oil in large skillet.
Add onion.
Cook until side of zucchini is lightly browned.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Top with tomatoes; cover and cook over medium heat until squash is tender and juice forms a fairly thick sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, one at a time, slightly beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sift flour and add to batter like biscuit dough.

Roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven until slightly brown. Use enough flour for rolling consistency or flour hands and roll into ball as you would a biscuit.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into ball.
Chill.
Press in 1/3 to 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Serve with favorite crackers.
Blend with hands.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Blend in blender until creamy; store in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix unflavored gelatine, spices and salt; blend in eggs, beaten with milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 10 minutes. Blend in pumpkin.
turn into prepared crust; chill until firm. Garnish, if desired, with whipped cream and pecans.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Freeze Butterfinger bars.
When frozen, place in plastic bag and crush.
Pull apart the angel food cake into small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together margarine, egg yolks and powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over angel food cake pieces and place Butterfinger bars on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese and pasta wedges
directions: Cook the spaghetti in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain, rinse in cold water, drain.
For sauce, cook 3 tablespoon green onion in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon thyme. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: dried beef balls
directions: Put dried beef into blender or food processor and make crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup to roll the finished balls in.
Mix everything else together by hand and form 2 balls.
After rolling balls in crumbled dried beef, refrigerate overnight.
Serve as a spread for crackers.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Crumble sausage meat over medium heat into a 12-inch frying pan. Add onion and cook until onion is limp and sausage is well browned, about 10 minutes. Discard fat and stir in sauce, mushrooms and olives. Heat until bubbly, then pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Arrange Mozzarella over top. Blend eggs, milk, oil, flour and salt until smooth. Evenly pour over Mozzarella, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in 400° oven until crust is puffed and golden, about 25 minutes. Cut into squares at once.

title: oriental beef(great for deer meat)
directions: Cut beef into serving pieces.
Slice scallions diagonally and place in bowl with beef.
Crush garlic.
Add to mixture.
Mix in rest of ingredients with hands.
Allow to marinate at least 3 hours.
Cook as desired.
Great on the grill!

title: vol au vent
directions: Bake the pastry shells in the oven as shown on the box.
On the stove in a pot, empty the can of chicken and mushrooms, adding 1/2 to 3/4 of the can of milk.
Cut the chicken up in pieces, adding it to the pot.
Stir everything together.
Heat it up on low to medium for a few minutes.
Pour on top of the hot pastry shells.
Serve with mashed potatoes and any kind of vegetables. Kids love it! Serves 3 to 5 persons.

title: italian chicken breasts
directions: Place dressing in large container and dip chicken breasts (one at a time and coating well) into dressing.
Leave chicken in container of dressing.
Cover and place in refrigerator to marinate 4 to 6 hours.
After marinated, dip chicken into egg and roll in flour seasoned with Season-All spice.
Deep-fry 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown and crispy.
Chicken breasts will be very tender and juicy when done.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Bone and cut into small pieces. Spread over buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix the soup and sour cream together.
Then spread over chicken.
Crush crackers, mix with poppy seed and spread over soup.
Melt margarine and drizzle over casserole evenly.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix together. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Brush edges of pie shell with water before baking to keep crust from getting too brown while waiting for coconut to brown.
Bake at 350° until filling is lightly browned, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until veggies are tender, stirring often.
Add spaghetti.
Heat through.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Put 4 cups of angel food cake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling over cake.
Place 4 cups of angel food cake on top.
Combine the pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat together and spoon over cake.

title: nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients except nuts; beat hard for 30 seconds (batter may be lumpy).
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until a toothpick comes out dry.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: cherry-nut slices
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour slowly, mixing well. Stir in nuts and cherries.
Chill. Divide dough into 3 parts.
Shape into rolls 10-inches long. Wrap in wax paper sprinkled with powdered sugar. Chill 3 hours or until firm. Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on ungreased sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are slightly brown.
Do not overbake.

title: yummy carrot salad
directions: Use fine grater and grate carrots. Put into medium sized salad bowl, adding the sugar, pineapple, raisins and mayonnaise; toss well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hobo meatball stew
directions: In a bowl, combine beef, 1 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a skillet over medium heat, brown meatballs on all sides; drain.
Place potatoes, carrots and onions in a slow cooker; top with meatballs.
Combine catsup, water, vinegar, basil and remaining salt and pepper; pour over meatballs. Cover and cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: super fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, mix pineapple, oranges, strawberries and bananas.
Pour pie filling over fruit and stir until just mixed. Chill.
Yields 2-quart bowl full.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleomargarine and sugar.
Add eggs and sour milk.
Add sifted ingredients, soda, salt and flour.
Mash bananas and mix well.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Place dates, magarine, salt and baking soda into boiling water.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Cool.
Mix sugar into mixture and add flour gradually.
Fill greased cans (soup size) about 3/4 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes about 6 cans.

title: pork pie
directions: Simmer first 6 ingredients 4 hours, then add potatoes.
Put in pie crust.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix well the butter, 1/2 cup sugar and remaining ingredients. Chill several hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll at once in confectioners sugar. Cool; roll again in sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.
These can be frozen.

title: coconut pudding
directions: Add all ingredients.
Place over medium heat and stir.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut, then pour into baked pie shell.

title: gene's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 11 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Spread thin layer of catsup over before cooking.

title: cheese ham balls
directions: Mix well.
Then form into 2 balls.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Before serving you can roll in chopped pecans or almonds.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Dip 18 corn tortillas in sauce. Add remaining sauce to meat mixture. Layer tortilla, meat and shredded cheese three times. Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: dilled salmon pie
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk, the beaten egg, onion, butter or margarine and salt until crumbs are moistened. Add salmon and mix thoroughly. Turn into a greased 8-inch pie plate.
Prepare instant potatoes according to package directions, omitting milk. Beat in the remaining egg.
Spoon around edge of pie.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve wedges with warm Dill Sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown meats; drain well.
Add spices and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on slice of party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix one box of corn bread mix according to box directions. Place in casserole dish.
Cover mixture with sliced peppers.
Pour one can of sweet cream-style corn on top of mixture.
Grate cheese and pour over mixture.
Mix second box of corn bread mix and pour over mixture.
Bake in oven until golden brown.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together lightly all ingredients.
Form into small balls. Brown in bacon fat. Remove from pan. Drain fat.
Make a gravy with flour and water, adding one bouillon cube.
Add meat balls and simmer slowly or place in oven at 250° for 1 hour.

title: northumberland salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple (undrained) and pistachio pudding. Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: calabacita
directions: Brown fryer in deep saucepan in 3 tablespoons shortening.
Add chopped onion and tomato and brown.
Add squash, corn and seasonings to taste.
Add 4 tablespoons tomato sauce.
Cover and cook for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix together the sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add the onion juice and stir.
Beat the salad oil in with a mixer. Add the poppy seed last.
Store in tight jar in refrigerator.

title: cherry burst
directions: Combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Fill pie crust with mixture.
Freeze until firm (2 to 3 hours).
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix until dough forms a ball.
Shape into balls, using 1 teaspoon each.
Flatten to about 2-inch size with hand.
Bake for 8 minutes.

title: baked celery
directions: Line casserole with half the bread crumbs.
Mix other ingredients and pour over crumbs.
Cover with other half of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together; sift into butter. Beat.
Add oats; mix well.
Add nuts last and stir in.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 16-inch greased pan.

title: spicy beef sandwiches
directions: *Makes enough for a large crowd.
Use lesser amounts of spice for smaller roasts.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs to mixture.
Mix soda and flour.
Mash bananas and add alternately with flour to batter. Add nuts and vanilla.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown
onion
and
green
pepper
with	small amount of cooking
oil.
Add	hamburger
and	brown.	Drain off fat.	In slow cooker, mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste and puree.
Add all spices.
Add
ground beef mixture.
Let simmer as long as you want.
(I
usually	simmer	3 to 4 hours.) Cook spaghetti noodles according to directions.
Pour sauce over noodles.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix all liquid ingredients together.
Gradually stir liquid ingredients with dry ingredients. Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Rinse and hull the strawberries; then measure.
Place a layer of berries in a pan, then a layer of sugar, until all ingredients are used.
Let stand overnight or until sugar is dissolved.
Place over heat, bring to a boil and cook about 10 minutes.
Pour into a bowl and let stand until the next day; then fill jelly glasses and seal.

title: glarch
directions: Put the glue in an old plastic container and add food coloring if you choose.
Pour in liquid starch a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Keep stirring until mixture holds together like putty, then test with your fingers.
If it's too sticky add more starch until smooth and rubbery.
Have fun playing, pulling and stretching.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.
No refrigeration required.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients and set aside.
Blend eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together; add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: wild rice and chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.

Melt oleo in large saucepan. Add onion and saute over low heat until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add half and half and chicken broth. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in chicken, pimento, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry on a cloud
directions: At high
speed,
beat
egg whites with cream of tartar, just until
soft
peaks form when beater is raised.
Gradually beat in 1
cups sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Continue beating until
soft
peaks form.
Meringue should be shiny and moist. Spread in
bottom and up sides of lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake
at
275° for 60 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave in oven overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well after each addition.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil and fry onion and garlic until transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, sugar and spices.
Bring to boil, then lower temperature and simmer for 2 hours.
You can also add meat balls or fried Italian sausage to your sauce before simmering.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Stir all
together
until
melted
over low heat.
Then stop stirring and boil one minute.
(Let boil up real bubbly.) Take off heat
and cool.
Add a pinch of salt and the vanilla. Beat until creamy.
This
makes
a
very
creamy frosting for cakes.

title: butternut squash
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and drizzle over casserole.
Add topping.

title: gingerbread pound cake
directions: Let margarine or butter and eggs stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, ginger and cinnamon; set aside.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended well.
Chill and serve.

title: batter for deep frying
directions: Mix in bowl.
Make well in center.
Add oil.
Gradually whisk in beer.
Work from center out.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks.
Fold gently into batter just before ready to use.

title: spiced tea
directions: Shake well.
Add 2 teaspoons per cup or to taste.
Add water. Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken or turkey broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice.

Make cream sauce of 2 tablespoons butter, flour, salt, milk and cheese. Add turkey strips to cream sauce and spoon over the broccoli. Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and 1 tablespoon melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs until well combined.
Stir in raisin bran cereal, orange peel and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, zucchini and nuts; mix well.
Spread evenly in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tests done.
Cool.
Serve plain or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tarter sauce
directions: Blend all together.
Serve with fish, pork chops or steak.

title: orange pineapple bavarian mold
directions: Drain fruits.
Measure 3/4 cup combined syrups.
Dissolve sugar and jello in boiling water.
Add orange rind and measured syrups.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend Cool Whip and jello mixture; chill until thickened.
Fold in fruits; pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.

title: new orleans style boil
directions: Fill the large pot 1/2 full of water.
Add bag of crab/shrimp boil and 2 to 4 tablespoons salt.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 5 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll dough as making pie crust using flour, shortening, salt and water.
Roll in one large sheet.
Spread apples over and add cinnamon and half the sugar over top.
Roll dough as for jelly roll.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch wide pieces and place on sides in baking dish.
Add remaining sugar.
Cover with boiling water and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: lefsa
directions: Boil peeled potatoes in salted water.
Rice the ptoatoes, whole hot, in flat pan.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
Place Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Pour soup (wine optional) mixture over chicken evenly.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken mixture. Evenly drizzle margarine over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waffles
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg yolks which have been mixed together.
Mix until batter is smooth and then add melted butter.
Last, fold in carefully the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Another tablespoon of sugar may be added to sweeten waffles as desired.
Use waffle iron to cook.
Butter as removed.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Salt, pepper and garlic powder the chicken.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice, milk, sugar and curry. Beat well.
Marinate chicken in sour cream mixture for 2 hours. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch foil-lined baking dish.
Grease foil before placing chicken in it.
Pour marinating sauce over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef pot roast with gravy:
directions: Coat meat with flour, put in frying pan.
Cook meat until flour is brown on both sides in hot oil.
Add meatloaf seasoning, pepper and salt, then add water.
Let simmer for 2 1/2 hours, until tender.
If desired, add vegetables in the last 45 minutes.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cook meat, onions and garlic until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 1/2 hour or longer.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix together.
This is delicious with fried fish.

title: peasant bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add oleo gradually.
Add water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in flour for soft dough.
Cover let rest for 45 minutes.
Turn out on floured board and knead.
Mold into 3 loaves.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise, bake approximately 25 minutes at 400°.
Brush loaves with butter last 5 minutes of baking.

title: south of the border soup
directions: Cook chicken in 1 1/2-quart water with onion, garlic and bay leaf until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove chicken, reserve broth.
Pick meat from bones.
Skim fat from reserved broth.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine all ingredients together and serve with cooked rice and cornbread.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 170 calories per serving, 6% calories come from fat.

title: fiddleheads with hollandaise
directions: Place yolks in top of double boiler over medium heat.
Slowly add in the water, whisking constantly until yolks thicken.
Remove from heat and whisk in lemon juice.
Slowly whisk in all butter. Place back in double boiler over very low heat, while preparing fiddleheads.
Divide cooked fiddleheads in individual plates and pour equal amounts of Hollandaise over.
Serve immediately.

title: carrot-zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl, beat brown sugar with oil until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time until blended.
Add milk; beat about 2 minutes. Mix in 1/3 of the flour mixture and then 1/2 of carrots and 1/2 of zucchini.
Repeat, ending with flour, mixing until just combined. Pour into pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Combine first three ingredients and refrigerate in covered container 24 hours.
Drain and add sugar and vinegar.
Refrigerate 24 hours and then freeze.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line 14-inch pizza pan with cookie slices, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry citrus sparkler
directions: In blender, combine orange and lemon juice, strawberries, ice and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 4 (10 ounce) glasses. Fill slowly with soda.
Top each with scoop of vanilla ice cream. Garnish with strawberries if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: susan's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and sprinkle on top. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: german bean soup
directions: Cover beans and soak overnight.
Drain; cover with a large amount of water.
Add the ham bone and simmer until beans are almost soft.
Skim off fat.
Add vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Take out ham bone.
Leave the beans whole or serve well mashed.

title: pink squirrel fondue
directions: In saucepan combine ingredients.
Cook and stir over low heat until heated through.
Transfer to small fondue pot.
Place on fondue burger.
Arrange fruit on platter.
Dip fruit into fondue and enjoy.

title: pizza
directions: You take gogomly, thin bread and avecotos.
You take your cotos and bake thin for 20 minutes.
And bake your gogomly for 1 hare. And biy bread and heat it very good!

title: inexpensive pound cake
directions: The beauty of this recipe is that you just dump the ingredients in a bowl all at the same time and beat with a mixer until all are well blended.
Bake in greased tube cake pan 1 hour at 350°.
Add black walnuts if desired.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over prepared zucchini and onions in large bowl and let stand one hour, stirring occasionally.
In large saucepan, bring mixture to a boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Continue simmering as you quickly pack hot sterilized jars.
Makes sure vinegar solution tops pickles.
Seal.
Process 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: extra good barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces.
Brown in baking pan over medium heat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
Spoon sauce over ribs 2 or 3 times during baking.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake in 2 square 8 x 8-inch pans for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut in squares; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in that order.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tammie's "strawberry" cookies
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, combine sugar, butter, egg, dates, coconut and pecans; stirring constantly until thoroughly melted and blended together.
Remove from heat, stir in Rice Krispies.
With well-greased hands, shape mixture into strawberry shapes and roll in red sugar crystals.
Dip "stem" end in green crystals.

title: chocolate trifle dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool.
Make pudding.
Whip the cream.
In trifle bowl crumble 1/3 cake; spread with 1/3 pudding, 1/3 whipped cream and 1/3 crushed Heath or Skor bars.
Repeat 2 more times.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake 15 minutes until brown.
Serve warm. Makes about sixty 1-inch balls.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini custard
directions: Salt the zucchini slices and cook until tender. Drain well. Beat together the eggs, sour cream and pepper.
Place zucchini in a 1-quart casserole. Add 1/4 cup cheese to egg mixture and pour over zucchini. Dot with margarine and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate almond cheesecake
directions: Toast almonds that were put in processor until crumbly. (Almonds should be toasted in a 400° oven until brown.) Mix with 1/2 cup sugar, almond extract and melted butter.
Press in a spring-form pan that is sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: excellent pot roast
directions: Roll roast in flour and brown on all sides in oil in Dutch oven or heavy roaster.
Add broth, wine, tomato paste, crushed garlic, carrots, celery and onion.
Cook on top of stove 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and cook 1/2 hour more or until potatoes are done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries.
Cook cranberries with water until skins pop.
Then smash cranberries.
Add sugar, raspberry Jell-O, pineapple (drained), fresh orange juice and nuts.

title: apple bake
directions: Toss apples and cranberries with mixture of flour, sugar and cinnamon. Spread in greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix brown sugar, flour and cinnamon in a bowl. Mix butter until crumbly. Add pecans. Spoon over apple mixture. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Great Christmas brunch dish.

title: pork and tater pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute sausage and onion in skillet until well browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in soup, water and mixed vegetables.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil fryer; debone, cut up and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup with 3 cups of chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Cut up the boiled eggs and place on chicken.
Mix the oleo, flour and buttermilk together; spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: beef carbonade
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Season meat with a little salt and pepper.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover with onions.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Reserve 1/3 cup beer. Combine remaining beer and next 6 ingredients.
Pour over meat. Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat to a platter.
Keep warm.
Skim off excess fat from pan juices.
Remove bay leaf.
In saucepan, cook juices down to 2 cups.
Combine reserved beer and flour; stir into pan juices.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Serve over meat or pass gravy.

title: coconut crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; beat in sugar.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Coat pie dish with butter and use graham cracker crumbs to form crust.
Add mixture and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
After baked and cooled, slice 2 medium bananas on top and top with whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Add milk and salt.
Mix well.
Pour this mixture into large saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. Combine egg mixture, Eagle Brand milk and cream with vanilla. Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze and ripen at least 1 hour.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, milk and fruit together.
Pour over melted butter and bake.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken in foil
directions: For each individual serving of chicken, arrange on a large piece of aluminum foil:
chicken breast and 1 tablespoon orange juice.
Sprinkle generously with rosemary and/or basil.
Sprinkle with chopped green onion.
Place 3 to 5 chopped (cut with kitchen shears) apricots.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: grannie buster's venison roast
directions: For 24 hours, marinate venison in a crock which contains equal parts water and vinegar, enough to cover roast and the onions, bay leaves, peppercorns, celery seed and tarragon leaves.
Then remove roast and drain.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine water and sugar to make a simple syrup.
Freeze pineapple, lemon juice and orange juice.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 bottles 7-Up and cherries.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk. Mix until smooth. Add rest of milk and pudding mix. Mix well. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. Serves 8. Top with blueberry filling.

title: country farm potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut off some of top; scoop out potato.
Mash in bowl.
In hot oil, saute 1/4 cup onion and 1 1/4 cups green pepper.
Heat the milk and add the sauteed vegetables to this with the salt and black pepper and add 1/2 of the grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix all with mashed potatoes.
Fill shells and sprinkle the other half cup of shredded cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
(Can be prepared ahead of time for use.)
Reheat filled potato shells 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients, except ketchup and brown sugar, in a large bowl. Mix well; press evenly into a loaf pan. Combine ketchup and brown sugar in a small bowl, mix well. Spread mixture evenly over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Marinade chicken breasts at least 12 hours.
Cook on grill or boil.
Serve over rice for main course.
Can be made into sandwiches.

title: frozen fruitcake salad
directions: In mixing bowl, blend sour cream, whipped cream, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Put into 4 1/2 cup ring mold.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Unmold onto lettuce leaf-lined plate.
Garnish with more cherries.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: peach blossoms
directions: In
blender, mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add and blend enough ice cubes to make drink thick.

title: cheese - sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes or golden brown.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a soup pot.
Saute the onion. Add the diced celery and carrot.
Cook a little, allowing the vegetables to glaze slightly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in 2 tablespoons of flour.
Add pumpkin and stir.
Gradually add chicken broth, white pepper and sugar.
Bring to a boil, uncovered.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Better with reheating.

title: cherry delite
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chocolate bavarian torte
