directions: Mix cake and bake according to package directions; use 9-inch cake pans.
Let cake cool for 15 minutes and remove from pans.
In mixing bowl, mix cream cheese, brown sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Split each cake into 2 pieces. Spread 1st layer with frosting, then sprinkle chocolate chips. Place 2nd layer on top.
Repeat steps until all 4 layers are in place.
You can frost only the tops of the layers or the top and sides.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: apple-raisin salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice on apples to keep them from turning brown.
Drain the raisins and mix all ingredients gently together.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: amish fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Place everything in bowl then add sour cream.
Mix and let set in the refrigerator about 2 hours.

title: black bottoms
directions: In a small bowl, mix together cream cheese, egg, sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Fill mini-cupcake papers 1/2 full with chocolate mixture.
Then add 1/2 teaspoon cream cheese mixture on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Put tomatoes through sieve.
Add all ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.
Ladle into jars to within 1 inch of top.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Yields 6 pints.
Process:
pints 75 minutes, quarts 90 minutes.
10 pounds pressure

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat; drain. Then add seasoning. Set aside. Heat Ro-Tel tomatoes. While tomatoes are heating, cut cheese and add to tomatoes. When cheese is dissolved, mix the tomato mix with the meat. Put lettuce and fresh tomatoes into a large bowl. Break up chips and sprinkle over top. Pour cheese mixture over all and serve immediately.

title: oriental snack mix
directions: Combine margarine, soy sauce and spices.
Pour over combined cereal, noodles and almonds.
Mix well.
Spread in 15 x 10-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 cups.

title: seafood salad
directions: Boil shrimp and let cool.
Combine shrimp, crabmeat, celery (diced), bell pepper (diced), onion (diced), seasonings, eggs and then mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Mix well.
Cover and place in refrigerator to chill.
Cut shrimp and crab meat to desired size.

title: cajun bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight or for 8 hours. Drain. Add 2 quarts water. Bring beans to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer for 2 1/2 hours. In skillet, saute onion, garlic and sausage until sausage is brown. Drain excess grease. Add to beans with the tomatoes and Cajun flavor packet. Simmer 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste. Make a pan of corn bread and enjoy.

title: strawberries(large batch)
directions: Mix Jell-O and condensed milk. Add coconut and pecans. Form into the shape of a strawberry. Roll in pink sugar. Then dip bottom in green sugar for the stem.

title: cranberry apple dish
directions: Mix in big bowl.
Put in baking pan.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Put chicken into pot with onion, carrots, water and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups broth.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice banana in bottom of baked pie shell.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip and fold into cream cheese mixture. Pour on fruit-filled pie shell and top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, flavors and buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add German chocolate that has been softened.
Blend together well.
Cook in a 9-inch stem pan, that has been well greased and dusted with flour, about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove cake from pan while still hot and place under tight-fitting cake cover; leave covered until cold.

title: sister barbara's peaches n' cream
directions: Stir a scant 1/2 c. sugar into peaches; set aside.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, salt, corn starch and water.
Cook, stirring until clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add peach Jell-o.
Stir to dissolve. Allow to cool to room temperature.
When cool, add peaches.
Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Gradually add milk and continue to beat.
Fold in Cool Whip by hand.
Spread one half cream cheese mixture over the prepared crust.
Add all the peach mixture and top with remaining cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved graham cracker crumbs.
Chill.
Best made a day before serving.

title: watergate salad(low-calorie)
directions: Use pineapple juice to dissolve pudding with wire whip.
Add pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk well.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour sweetened peaches or other fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients and raisins in mixing bowl.
Make well in center after mixing well.
Add buttermilk; stir until lightly blended.
Use only enough buttermilk to make stiff dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead 5 times.
Form into ball and place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Pat to 8-inch circle, approximately 1 1/2 inches thick.
With floured knife, make large cross on top to prevent cracking.
Spread top of loaf with softened butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden and loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Serve hot with butter.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl. Add other ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cover with Sauce.

title: lasagna
directions: Crumble beef into a 2-quart baking dish and stir in onion. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain well and set aside.
Place lasagna noodles in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; cover with water and add 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 14 minutes.
Rearrange noodles after 7 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Stir the next 6 ingredients together and into beef mixture and mix well.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and 1/2 teaspoon of salt well.
Spread part of tomato sauce over bottom of dish.
Top with noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat with sauce, noodles, etc.
Top with Parmesan.
Cover and microwave on High for 13 to 18 minutes; rotate every 5 minutes.

title: louisiana cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cornstarch.
Add vanilla and mix well. Add flour and mix well, then add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 300° oven.
Check until slightly brown around the edge.
These cookies do not get brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except corn.
Add corn.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until lightly browned. Add broth, tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Fluff with fork. Serve with cheese, tortilla chips and sour cream, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven and punch holes on top of cake.
Pour half of sauce over cake.
When cool, remove from pan, turn over and cover cake with remaining sauce.

title: grilled chicken easy
directions: Pound chicken flat.
Stir dressing and seasonings together. Place chicken on grill, rack or broiler pan.
Brush with 1/2 of the sauce. Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Time may vary according to how thin chicken is.

title: macaroni and sausage bake
directions: Cook meat and onion until lightly browned.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Boil macaroni 7 minutes; drain.
Put on top of meat.
Combine soup and milk; heat.
Slowly stir into eggs. Add cheese; pour over macaroni and meat.
Mix corn flakes and butter; place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Cool.
Cut into pieces.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add broth, milk and soup; cook until thick.
Mix stuffing with butter and water as directions on package.
Grease 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken, sauce and stuffing in layers.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Serves 6. Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Cook and stir until thick about 10 minutes on low heat.
Remove pan.
Add 2 cups rice cereal and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Butter hands and roll dough in balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in coconut.
Place on wax paper to set.

title: fruit dream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use more or less coconut, pecans and vanilla yogurt. Quick and easy; always a hit!

title: creamed cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces and cook until tender. Drain and place in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook together a few minutes. Remove from heat and blend in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly and simmer until thickened.
Pour over cauliflower in casserole.
Combine last three ingredients and spoon on top, pressing down if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs (beaten) and beat until lemon-colored.
Combine sifted flour and baking powder; add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Take out of oven and cool for 10 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic clove in oil until onion is soft. Discard garlic.
Add green pepper and saute another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add stock, tomatoes and corn.
Mash 2 cups of beans and add to pot along with whole beans and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes.
If too watery, remove cover and cook for another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: early riser's biscuits
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Mix with water and Crisco.
Knead into biscuits.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Makes 24 rolls.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Use as a dip for sliced apples.
Can also be used to dip celery or crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all patty ingredients in a bowl. Form into 8 patties.
Fry patties in a lightly greased nonstick skillet over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes on each side until lightly browned.

title: potato bites
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes, but do not peel.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in oven at 400°.
Do not allow to burn!
Add potato cubes to pan of melted butter and spoon butter over to coat potatoes thoroughly. Sprinkle liberally with seasonings.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Serve chilled with chips or crackers.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and oleo until creamy.
Set aside. In bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan, spread nuts and coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Spread over nut mixture.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over unbaked cake at random.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook meat until tender, on low setting of crock-pot.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookieslincoln, nebraska
directions: Mix sugars together then blend in butter.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Simmer the onion in Crisco, then add remaining ingredients.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add catsup, relish, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Put margarine in a 1-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until melted.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend in milk.
Microwave on High until thickened, 3 to 6
minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.

title: cottage cheese dressing
directions: Sieve cottage cheese.
Add seasonings, chives and lemon juice. Whip nonfat dry milk and ice water until stiff.
Combine with cheese mixture.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens or use as a dip for raw vegetables.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: steak over rice
directions: Brown meat, onions and mushrooms in butter.
Stir in flour. Add 1 cup water, bouillon cubes, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook slowly 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: babe's apple cake
directions: Combine eggs,
sugars, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in oiled 13 x
9-inch
pan.
Sprinkle
with powdered sugar if desired.	You may
substitute
more
cinnamon for the nutmeg. You may also
add probably
less apples than called for but I dice them very fine.

title: bean biscuits
directions: Put beans in a large bowl.
Stir in just enough flour to make beans slightly thick.
Pour oil into skillet, just enough to cover bottom of skillet.
Drop bean mixture into skillet by spoonfuls until you reach the desired amount for each patty.
Cook over medium heat until both sides are brown.
Add more oil as necessary.
If desired, can add some chopped onions, green peppers and shredded cheese.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup chopped nuts in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Shape mixture into 2 logs about 8 inches long.
On waxed paper place chopped nuts and roll logs to cover completely.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 3 dozen (1/2 inch) slices.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In double boiler, melt marshmallows with oil, then mix with popcorn, gumdrops and nuts.
Put in angel food cake pan.

title: german pancakes
directions: Separate eggs.
Put yolks in bowl; add milk and then flour, stirring as flour is added.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until egg whites have peaks.
Fold into flour mixture.
Put small amount of butter and shortening in frying pan. When frying pan is hot, ladle in pancake mixture.
Turn pancake when edges begin to brown.
Serve with jam, applesauce or fruit compote.

title: stuffed tomato salad
directions: Carefully wash and peel the tomatoes.
Mix the filling together in the order given, blending well.
Cut tomatoes in tenths, cutting through the tomato almost to the bottom.
Place on a crisp leaf of lettuce and pile the stuffing onto the tomato. Makes 6.

title: walnut fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In large bowl, combine sugar, butter, egg yolks, orange rind and orange juice. Beat until well mixed. Stir in walnuts, coconut and raisins. Beat the egg whites until stiff. Fold into fruit/nut mixture. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is lightly browned and the filling is set. Cool completely before slicing.

title: vivian's pound cake
directions: Cream or beat butter; add sugar, eggs, then flour, milk and flavoring.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours; put cake in cold oven, then turn on temperature to 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours in tube cake pan.
This makes a big cake.

title: papa's baked beans
directions: Cook broccoli and onion, then drain off water. Cook rice as directed. Heat the soup. Add all ingredients together. Cook in oven at 350 degree for about 45 minutes.

title: wednesday night burgers
directions: Cook onion in small amount of butter; add ground chuck and brown.
Then add catsup, mustard and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste and add small amount of sugar (if desired).
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve hot on buns.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well. Cover tightly and chill at least 8 hours. Serve dressing over salad greens. Yield: 4 cups.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar. Add and mix well the eggs, coconut, nuts, vanilla wafers and vanilla. Bake in sheet cake pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: low calorie cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake in greased tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Stuffing/Filling:
Fix 4 servings of Stove Top stuffing, set aside until ready to use.

title: 4-layered casserole
directions: Mix ham loaf or meatloaf to your favorite recipe.
Layer in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese soup over top.
Spread mixed vegetables over cheese soup.
Top with a layer of Tater Tots.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Place lettuce in a large bowl.
Top with beans, tomatoes and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Layer remaining ingredients; toss lightly to combine.

title: "easy" treat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Cut Treet into small chunks and put into saucepan. Add onion and bell pepper; cook until tender. Add macaroni and mix. Lay cheese slices on top and as they melt, mix together.

title: homemade silly putty
directions: Mix well.
It needs to dry a bit before it is "workable."
It may not work well on a humid dry day.
This will bounce and pick up pictures.
Store in airtight container.

title: batter bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Pour in liquids and mix until completely moistened.
Plop into greased loaf pan.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Grate zucchini (about 2 cups).
Beat eggs and add to zucchini. Add cheese, flour, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix batter well.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Turn when light brown.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Put all ingredients into electric blender; mix and put in a bottle (fifth) and refrigerate for about a week or better.
Keeps for quite a while if refrigerated.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Whisk together all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High 10 minutes, whisking after 5 minutes.
Whisk again, then microwave on Medium-high for 5 minutes.
Whisk, then let stand, covered, about 20 minutes.
Makes 5 cups.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift together 3 times, the flour, sugars and baking powder. 4th time, sift over fruit and nuts and mix well.
Beat eggs well, add vanilla and cherry juice and mix well.
Add to fruit mixture. Hint:
Put in large bowl and mix well with hands.
Grease 2 (8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch) pans well and line bottoms with waxed paper.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
One big pan will bake for 2 hours.

title: hamburger bean supper
directions: Lightly brown hamburger and onions in butter.
Drain.
Combine with drained noodles and remaining ingredients in buttered 2 qt. casserole dish.

title: date cake(christmas cake)
directions: Sprinkle some extra flour over fruit and nuts.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients and liquids; blend with fruit and nuts.
Bake 2 1/4 hours at 250°.
Will make five 1-pound flat type coffee cans or your choice of containers.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until just firm.
Mix Ricotta cheese with egg, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Add a little salt and pepper to taste.

title: southern pecan pie(right from florida)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add
sugar,
dash
of salt and melted oleo. Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Decorate top with pecan
halves.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean when stuck into the center of the pie.

title: strawberry sundae
directions: Beat until stiff; fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread over crust mixture which is crumbled and in a cake pan.
Place in freezer overnight.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine cocoa, vanilla wafers, sugar and nuts.
Add corn syrup and bourbon.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Pinch off walnut sized pieces and roll into balls.
Roll balls in cocoa.
Serve.
Makes 50 to 60 balls.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Chop vegetables and rest of ingredients. Stir and refrigerate.

title: miss frances' squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine Jell-O, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Mix well. Chill 1 hour. Shape into strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
You can use leaves with pick from craft store or you can use decorator frosting in an aerosol can.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine the peas, onion, pickle, eggs, celery and grated cheese.
In a small bowl combine the sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over salad and stir.

title: taco salad
directions: Break up lettuce into pieces.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes, olives, cheese and hamburg together.
Add Doritos to mixture.
Add taco sauce, then Catalina dressing just before serving.
Enjoy!

title: sweet and sour broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower separately.
Cook fresh vegetables until tender-crisp.
Put into warm serving dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, mix broccoli, cauliflower, purple onion and red grapes or raisins, you may use both.
If you use red grapes, cut them into quarters.
Cut the broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets and chop the onion real fine.
Crumble bacon into the mixture.
In small mixing bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Add to vegetable mixture and stir well.
Chill overnight before serving.
Serves 8.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix together and chill.
Recipe can be doubled, tripled, etc. You can substitute any fruit jello.
I also make lime jello with crushed or chunked pineapple.
Nuts may be added.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: In large bowl, combine zucchini, biscuit mix, onion, cheese, parsley, salt, seasoned salt, oregano, pepper and garlic.
Add oil and eggs and beat thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until top is set.
Cool slightly and cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes about 30 appetizers.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and 2 crushed candy bars. Pour into crust. Top with other crushed candy bar and freeze for 2 hours.

title: baked pineapple toast
directions: Combine butter, sugar and pineapple.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with bread.
Beat eggs, milk and salt together; pour over bread.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Invert on heated serving platter.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: Cook
all ingredients, except butter and milk, over low heat until
well
done.	Add butter and milk.
Serve hot with crackers. Yields 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, salt, pepper, carrot, sour cream, soup and onion. Melt butter and combine with dressing mix.
Put half of dressing mix in 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Pour on squash mixture and then add the rest of the dressing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pet milk nut fudge
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, butter, marshmallow, salt and Pet milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbly all over top.
Boil and stir over medium heat 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in broken nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Press nut halves on top if desired.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into about 30 pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Add flour and baking powder.
Pour over baked mixture.
Bake 25 minutes more at 350°. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: snowball puffs
directions: Beat by hand all ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Cool.
Roll in your favorite jelly, then coconut.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Blend all together and put into greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Cut into bars and refrigerate.

title: microwaved glazed carrots and potatoes
directions: Heat butter for 30 seconds in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Stir in honey, lemon juice, carrots and potatoes.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap; cook 5 minutes on High.
Turn dish, stir, cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add salt.
Cover; let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients except rock salt into mixing bowl.
Mix until it is all mixed well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line.
Cover.
Add ice and rock salt until full.
When freezer stops, let sit 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter burst cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until creamy (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Add egg.
Beat well.
Turn mixer to low. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in peanut butter morsels.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Put in pie shell and bake until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Put water, onion, celery and bouillon on to boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add potatoes; continue cooking until potatoes are done.
Add cheese.
While it is melting, make a roux with margarine and flour, to thicken.
Add roux to soup mixture. Simmer a short while; remove from heat.
Add milk.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lightly saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese over top.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: cheddar corn chowder
directions: In a large stockpot over medium-high heat, cook the beacon and olive oil until the bacon is crisp, about 5 minutes.
Remove the bacon with a slotted spoon and reserve.
Reduce the heat to medium; add the onions and butter to the fat and cook for 10 minutes until the onions are translucent.
Stir in the flour, salt, pepper and turmeric and cook for 3 minutes.
Add the chicken stock and potatoes; bring to a boil and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes, until the potatoes are tender.
If using fresh corn, cut the kernels off the cob and blanch them for 3 minutes in boiling salt water.
Drain.
If using frozen corn, you can skip this step. Add the corn to the soup, then add the half and half and Cheddar. Cook for 5 more minutes, until the cheese is melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot with a garnish of bacon.

title: crusty chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until just tender; drain.
Arrange in greased 11 x 17-inch baking pan. Arrange chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken.
Pour butter over soup mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: mini quiche
directions: Generously grease muffin cups.
Separate dough and press into muffin cups.
Divide shrimp evenly into shells.
In small bowl, combine egg, half and half, brandy, pepper, pimento and parsley flakes.
Spoon approximately 1 tablespoon mixture into each shell. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° approximately 20 minutes until puffy and light golden brown.
Cool slightly; remove from muffin cups.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a roll and chill.
When ready to use, slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix ingredients together and then mix in cooked carrots. Best if set over night.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake cake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan as directed. Mix cream cheese, instant pudding and 2 cups cold milk.
Beat until mixed well; let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon on cooled cake. Spread drained pineapple on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and ground nuts.
Will serve 12 to 16.

title: boneless tortilla chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut chicken into strips.
Mix crushed chips with seasoning mix in a large bowl.
Beat eggs and combine with milk.
Dip chicken into milk and dredge in chips.
After chicken is covered, place in a greased shallow baking dish. Drizzle with melted margarine and place in oven.
Cook approximately 12 to 15 minutes, or until chicken is completely done.
Wonderful when served with your favorite salsa.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Put in 2 (8-inch) layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes, approximately 1/4-inch thickness. Mix all other ingredients in bowl.
Toss tomato slices in this mixture to coat well.
Fry these in hot cooking oil, until browned.

title: catherine posio's famous pasties
directions: Put flour and salt into a bowl.
Using a pastry cutter or knives, cut shortening into flour until pieces are the size of small peas.
Gradually add the 7-Up and egg mixture until the crust forms a ball (you may not need all of the liquid).
Cover and chill crust.

title: quick bake fruit pie
directions: Mix everything together except butter and fruit.
Pour half of the butter into batter.
Leave other half in baking dish.
Add fruit and then pour other half of batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until slightly browned.

title: karo fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry mixture until smooth.	Pour into pan.	Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat undrained pineapple in saucepan.
Add gelatin. Stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add buttermilk and whipped topping.
Mix well. Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in 2 cups salted water, covered, for 8 minutes. Drain.
Fry four slices bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving grease.
Add brown sugar and flour to grease; blend.
Add water, vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add bacon and cabbage; heat thoroughly.

title: chicken squash casserole
directions: Mixture:
Chicken, soup, sour cream and chestnuts.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together in skillet until meat is done and crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season with garlic salt and hot sauce to taste.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm and serve with chips.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Make jello with hot, then cold water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling to jello.
Let mixture set until firm.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Pour hot water over Jell-O;
stir let stand until cool. Add oil and eggs to cake mix, then the cooled Jell-O.
Pour in rectangle 2-inch deep pan.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix up first 4 ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts.
Put in greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: my sandwich
directions: Slice off top of bread and hollow out inside.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour inside hollowed out bread.
Put top back on bread. Wrap in foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hershey's light chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8-inch round pans with cooking spray.
In bowl, stir flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In saucepan, melt corn oil spread; stir in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan; stir.
Add dry ingredients; whisk until well blended.
Pour evenly into pans. Bake 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean. Cool.
Fill and frost top.
Refrigerate. Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken in white sauce
directions: Melt butter; add salt and pepper.
Whisk in flour.
Add milk and broth and simmer until thick.
Pour white sauce over chicken in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine juices with ginger ale.
Spoon in sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small balls.
Roll in flour and brown.
Put into a casserole.
Cover with soup, blended with 1 can of water.

title: red cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage as finely as possible.
Grate apple (without peel).
Place apple and onion in small amount of oil in heavy kettle or pot.
Cook just enough to glaze.
Add cabbage, on fairly high heat, stirring constantly until cooked down in size a little. Add brown sugar, honey, cloves, vinegar and salt.
Turn down heat and slowly cook mixture, covered, about 3/4 to 1 hour.
During cooking, stir 3 to 4 times to prevent burning on bottom of pan. Taste cabbage; a little more of each ingredient may be required and added at this time until the taste is "just right".

Place finished cabbage in dish with cover; store in refrigerator or cool place. Cabbage is best prepared hours ahead of time, stored and reheated just before serving, giving all ingredients time to blend properly. Reheat and enjoy!

title: brian's pineapple dessert
directions: Put 2 slices pineapple on plate.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top of pineapple.
Add spoon of mayonnaise and add a cherry on top.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Beat eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add dry mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° till done.

title: chicken casserole(serves 20)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and more almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
It freezes well!

title: cucumber salad
directions: Thinly slice cucumber into medium size bowl.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix to dissolve sugar.
Serve chilled.

title: pignolia(cookies)
directions: Beat egg whites with almond paste. Set aside. Sift together flour, sugars and salt.
Stir into almond paste mixture. Form dough into logs approximately 2-inches long and roll in nuts to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, make a well in center of mixture; set aside.
Combine egg and brown sugar in a medium bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add bananas, raisins, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Let cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery for 7 minutes; drain.
Mix celery, soup and water chestnuts.
Pour into casserole.
Mix crackers and almonds with melted butter.
Spoon over celery mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and clean peppers; parboil and cool.
Mix ingredients. Stuff peppers and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover, pour chili sauce over peppers and bake 15 minutes more.

title: cheese-nut bread
directions: Sift flour twice with baking powder, salt and sugar; add cheese and pecans, mixing thoroughly.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Stir quickly until dry ingredients are dampened.
Batter should not be smooth.
Pour into buttered 8 x 4 x 3-inch bread pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool bread on wire rack before slicing.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle meat, cheese and onion in the bottom of the pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed 1 minute. Pour into plate and bake until brown (about 50 to 55 minutes).
I like this best with sausage. Serves 6 people.

title: brandied mocha
directions: Heat uncovered in microwave oven until hot, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir.
Pour into cups and top with whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a low casserole dish.
Crumble crackers in a bowl.
Melt butter; stir into crackers.
Mix all liquids together.
Layer crackers and oysters, starting and ending with crackers.
Pour liquid mixture over all.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix to a smooth batter the margarine, eggs, soda, sugar, flour and buttermilk.
Then add orange slice candy, coconut, chopped dates, nuts and grated orange peel.
Bake in tube pan for 2 hours at 250°.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute bacon, diced, until almost crisp.
Saute onion in bacon fat until crisp.
Drain fat.
Combine bacon, onion, pork and beans, ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, A.1., mustard and molasses.
Pour into one-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 55 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Makes six servings.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Beat the sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla at high speed for about 3 minutes. Add flour and milk alternately at low speed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
This is good baked in a large iron skillet. The recipe can be cut in half. When you get ready to serve, use the sauce when you cut into wedges.

title: oven french toast
directions: Arrange bread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Mix milk, salt, eggs, sugar and cinnamon. Dip bread in mixture and put on pan. Drizzle remaining egg mixture over the bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake on a preheated greased cookie sheet. Bake at 500° for 5 minutes, then turn over bread and bake 4 more minutes. Sprinkle confectioners sugar over bread after baking and serve.

title: pasta with peas
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook slowly until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper; simmer about 10 minutes.
Add peas together with another 1 1/2 cans of water; simmer about 5 minutes.
Toss this mixture with cooked pasta.
Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a soft boil.
Remove and add 1 pound of peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water (not boiling).
Stir in milk, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla extract. Cool until mixture can be shaped into small balls.
Dip each ball into sweetened cocoa powder.
Cool and store in a can.

title: perfect peanut brittle
directions: Boil the sugar, peanuts and Karo to hard crack stage.
Remove from fire.
Add butter; stir until melted.
Add soda and stir well.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
As it cools, pull from sides until very thin.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together to form ball.
Mash ball flat onto serving tray to round shape.
Mix last 4 ingredients using small amounts of taco sauce at a time, just enough to make ingredients moist.
Spread this over cream cheese mixture.
Top all with small amount taco sauce.
Dip into with large corn chips.

title: jumbo cookies
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and carefully add cornflakes.
Drop batter from teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove cookies from pan immediately.

title: green tomato raspberry jam
directions: *Strawberry Jell-O can be used in place of raspberry.

title: dill seed bread
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Let rise to double.
Punch down.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour and knead well.
Shape into 2 loaves.
I use 2 medium sized bread pans.
Let rise to top of pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Butter and salt top of crusts.
Cover tightly with foil.
These make great toast.

title: shoe-horn cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll into a long roll.
Cut into small pieces and form into crescents.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar after baking.
(Kind of like "wedding cookies".)

title: deep dish cavatina
directions: Prepare your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Cook the three different kinds of macaroni.

In a large baking pan, layer the elbow macaroni, spaghetti sauce, Colby cheese, then add the shell macaroni, spaghetti sauce and American cheese, then add the rotini macaroni, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° just long enough to melt cheese.
This is a nice one dish casserole to serve with a salad and French bread.

title: wassail
directions: Boil spices 1 minute in 2 cups apple cider.
Add rest of cider, frozen juices and brown sugar.
Heat to desired temperature or heat to simmer.

title: crab snacks
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread the mixture on each muffin half.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cut each muffin into quarters.
Broil about 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread hash browns on top of melted margarine.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion (optional) and cheese together in a bowl, then spread mixture on top of potatoes.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in bowl, then add the crushed corn flakes together; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Brown meats; add other ingredients and simmer until fairly thick.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and cold water.
Gradually pour into boiling water, stirring constantly.
Return to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour into loaf pan.
Plastic wrap directly on mush will keep it from drying on top.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: simple jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage until almost done.
Throw onions in; saute.
Add tomatoes and paste and cook until brown.
Fill can of paste with water.
Simmer until cooked.
Cook 2 cups rice in rice cooker and add to sauce.

title: hot heroes
directions: Combine cheese, oregano, olives, mushrooms, onions, oil and tomato sauce in large bowl; mix well.
Spread cheese mixture on bread slices; broil until bubbly.

title: stuffing for chicken or turkey
directions: Cook pork sausage until done.
Boil celery, onion and butter in water until tender.
Combine the sausage, celery, onion and sage with croutons.
Mix together and make sure it's real moist. Bake about 1 hour at 350° in a greased casserole dish.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in dates, pecans and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°, about 15 minutes.
Cut, while warm, and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion, chili powder and green pepper in butter.
Add soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Then add boned and cut up chicken. Soak tortillas in cool chicken broth.
In a 2-quart casserole, line bottom with 1/2 the soaked tortillas, then 1/2 the mixture, some grated cheese and then repeat.
Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: eclair dessert squares
directions: Butter bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Line with graham crackers.

title: l's hot pigtails
directions: Combine pig tails, salt and pepper to taste and crushed red pepper (depending on how hot you like it) and water.
Bring to boil.
Turn down on medium and let cook for about an hour or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the usual order.
Roll into log and cool. Cut in 1/4-inch slices and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: white fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil so the foil extends over two opposite sides of the pan.
Lightly grease or butter the foil.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, bring mixture to a boil. Continue boiling and stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Creme, candy coating and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Fold in pecans or candies.
Pour into prepared pan.
Let stand several hours or overnight, until firm.
Remove fudge from pan by lifting foil.
Remove foil from fudge.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: layered taco dip for large group
directions: Peel and mash avocados, add 1 chopped tomato,salt, pepper,lemon juice, garlic powder,minced onion and hot pepper sauce and set aside. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning and set aside. On large platter spread refried beans as 1 layer of dip. Next spread the avocados mixture. Cover with sour cream and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle with 4 chopped tomatoes, green onions and cheese.
Top with olives. Serve with tostados or chips.

title: fried corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in the butter or bacon drippings for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel.
Add sugar and butter.
Make well.
Add to this the 2 eggs, well beaten.
Add enough sweet milk to thin to a medium mixture.
Bake in uncooked pie shell until done.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat with onion, green pepper and seasons. Drain off grease. Mix in pepperoni, olives, mushrooms and sauce. Heat until hot. Add to 9 x 13 greased pan with noodles; stir. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with parsley (optional). Bake until cheese is browned at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate ripple divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in a heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Cook to a hard ball stage without stirring.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture loses gloss and will hold shape.
Fold in chocolate bits quickly and drop from teaspoon onto buttered waxed paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: curried shrimp salad
directions: In large saucepan over high heat, bring 6 cups water to boil. Add shrimp; when water returns to boil, cook until pink and opaque, about 3 minutes.
Drain well; allow to cool.
Chop shrimp coarsely. In medium size bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice and curry; blend well.
Stir in shrimp, celery, carrot and scallion. Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with lettuce or apple slices.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving with 2 slices whole wheat bread:
135 calories, 20 grams protein, 4 grams fat, 5 grams carbohydrate, 201 milligrams sodium, 142 milligrams cholesterol.

title: bread sticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water in large bowl.
Add oil. Stir in flour gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Roll out dough into pencil thin strips; cut into sticks.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Dip sticks in butter.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Let rise in warm place until light.
Bake at 400° until golden.
Garlic or onion may be used to season.

title: dickie's "oatmeal plus" cookies
directions: Substitute for pecans:
Any nut, i.e., walnut, almond, etc.

title: honey pancakes with strawberries
directions: Slice strawberries, sprinkle with sugar and let stand.
Melt butter; cool.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat together milk, lemon juice, egg, 2 tablespoons honey and the cooled butter.
With a few quick strokes, combine wet and dry ingredients.
Heat a large frying pan brushed with oil over medium high heat.
Pour batter by scant 1/4 cupfuls into hot pan.
Cook until bubbles burst.
Flip and cook until golden.
Remove from pan and repeat with remaining batter, brushing pan with oil as needed. Serve pancakes with strawberries and drizzle with remaining honey.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Roll chicken breast and dried beef or ham tightly.
Wrap each with bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Place in large baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over breasts.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours and serve with rice.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour. Add salt.
Cut in Crisco.
To slightly beaten egg yolk, add lemon juice.
Sprinkle water on flour mix.
Combine. Form into ball.
Roll with rolling pin for crust.
Makes a 9-inch pie crust.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until vegetables are tender.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cubed steak and gravy
directions: Flour cubed steak.
Brown in shortening over medium heat. Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
(Can transfer to baking dish and bake 1 1/2 hours.)

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place all in a buttered dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 20 minutes, cover with crushed, buttered cornflakes.
Serves 10 to 12 or more.

title: sauce-pineapple chutney
directions: In small saucepan combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cut tenderloin or turkey in half.
Serve chutney over tenderloin or other meats.

title: spinach casserole
directions: With mixer, combine butter and flour.
Add eggs; beat well. Add Ricotta cheese; beat well.
Add Cheddar cheese and stir.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with croutons.
Place casserole in oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Prepare cream of chicken soup as directed on can.
Use milk or water.
Bring to boil.
Pour into round casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Add corn, onion, sugar, margarine and pepper and mix well.
Add Jiffy mix.
Can be cooked in a bowl set in water in the crock-pot on high for an hour, then on low about 3 to 4 hours until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Can also be cooked in 325° oven for about an hour.
If cooked in oven, place pudding bowl in a pan of water in center of oven.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix every thing together.
May serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine the eggs and tomato juice.
Stir all ingredients except ground chuck, ham and cheese, into the egg mixture.
Add the ground chuck and mix well.
Put onto waxed paper to form a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on meat and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Start from short end and roll up.
Place roll seam down in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Overlap cheese on top of meat and put back in oven to melt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine soft cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, milk and oregano, mixing until well blended.
(Use mixer or food processor, if desired.)
Shape into a ball (will be sticky).
Place in a bowl and chill for several hours.
Later, remove from refrigerator and roll in snipped parsley
(fresh if possible) or finely chopped nuts.

title: sauce for meat loaf
directions: Combine
all ingredients;
simmer for 10 or 15 minutes. Serve over your favorite meat loaf.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes, onions and garlic.
Place in pan and add salt, then add 3 trays of ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain liquid off and wash good 3 or 4 times.
Drain again.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spices on and bring to a good boil.
Then put in cukes and boil for 10 minutes.
Put in jars while hot and seal.

title: onion-cheese canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Blend Parmesan cheese with mayonnaise. Remove crust from bread.
Slice onion. Put one slice of onion on each slice of bread and spread with mixture of cheese and mayonnaise.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 sections and place on cookie sheet.
Bake until mixture begins to brown.

title: spinach dressing
directions: Crumble bacon and set aside.
Discard drippings.
In pan, mix oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and sugar.
Mix well and heat thoroughly.
Pour over cleaned and dried spinach leaves and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham crust.

title: lois murray's nut bread
directions: Mix and sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg.
Add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and flour alternately to the egg and sugar mixture.
Add chopped nuts, black walnuts or pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes, then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: krispy chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Add butter and using pastry blender or fork, cut in the butter until mixture is crumbly. Lightly press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and jalapeno peppers very fine.
Mix all ingredients together in Tupperware-type container with lid and refrigerate. Serve with chips.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Mix together lightly.
Bake for 3/4 hour (45 minutes) at 375°. Serve with white sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter, flour, salt, milk and cook to thicken.
Add the yolks of eggs and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining ingredients to egg mixture then fold into egg whites.
Put in a casserole and bake at 350 degrees until a knife goes through it as is stiff.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine, salt and milk in a pan. Place over heat and bring to a hard boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and pecans. Blend well and spread evenly in a long, shallow pan.
Cool until firm.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Mix cracker crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine; reserve. Beat cake mix, water, oil and eggs in a large bowl on low speed until moistened. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour about 2 1/3 cups batter in pan.
Sprinkle with 2 cups reserved crumb mixture.
Pour remaining batter in pan and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool and glaze.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk until thick (stirring). Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell that you have sprinkled coconut on bottom.
Pour.
Add more coconut on top of filling.
Cover with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add 1/3 cup sugar to egg whites.
Cover with more coconut and brown in 425° oven until nice and brown.
Let cool before cutting.

title: party mix(diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Slowly melt margarine in shallow pan. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add Chex cereals.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Two-thirds cup equals 1 bread and 1 fat.

title: "pinto bean pie"(mock pecan)
directions: Using a spoon (not a mixer), mix together sugar and pinto beans.
Stir in melted margarine.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add coconut and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cook bacon and crumble up.
Mix cream cheese, onions, bacon, and worcestershire sauce. Mix well and shape into a ball and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: seafood brochettes(serves 4)
directions: Remove the veins from the prawns.
Combine the white wine, lime juice, Tabasco sauce, olive oil and cilantro for the marinade.
Add the seafood to the marinade and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin tin with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
In large bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
Stir in last 4 ingredients.
Add dry mixture and blend.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 18 muffins.
Delicious!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Spread over cooled cake.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top if you like.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Layer:
Cube cake and put 1/2 in bottom of bowl.
Pour 1/2 orange juice, 1/2 pudding/whipped cream and 1/2 fruit.
Repeat and serve.

title: italian beef stir-fry
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in wok for 1 minute.
Add sliced beef (1/2 at a time). Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove.
Add zucchini; stir-fry until tender.
Return beef to wok with tomatoes and dressing.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Lay chicken flat.
Place a piece of cheese, then ham on chicken.
Roll up chicken.
Hold shape by sticking a toothpick in it.
Place in pan.
Pour mushroom sauce over it.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: micro veggies
directions: Peel veggies; cut in 2-inch pieces.
Rinse.
In a microwave dish place all ingredients.
Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes. Check for doneness; stir and redo, if needed.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Reserve some pecans to roll cheese ball in or sprinkle on top and sides.

title: brown rice
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until all broth is absorbed.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: You will need one buttered plate.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan for 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Cheese may be placed on top and returned to oven until it melts.

title: fruit crisp(low-fat)
directions: Combine fruit, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss well.

title: bacon and cheddar muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch with paper baking cups.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and bacon just until moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in cheese and bacon.
Divide batter among muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes; cool 15 minutes.

title: v.i.p. pecan pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients together, adding nuts last.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
When pie is done, outer edge of filling is set and center is slightly soft.
When cool, serve plain, or topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spicy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine cake mix, oats and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on a cookie sheet.

title: sausage bean burritos
directions: In a large saucepan, cook sausage, green pepper and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain.
Stir in beans, rice and 1 cup of salsa.
Mix well.
Spread about 1/2 cup of sausage mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with 1 T. cheese.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking dish.
Top with remaining salsa, cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 min.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5-10 min. longer or until cheese is melted.
Yield: 10 Burritos.

title: my favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and parsley. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
In blender container, place tomatoes and cover.
Blend on high speed until chopped (30 seconds).
Add to onion mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.

title: throw together vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan.
Cook on high until it starts to bubble.
Turn down on medium and cook 2 to 3 hours.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add pecans.
In small bowl, mix egg, vanilla and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
In small bowl, add baking soda to pineapple; stir. (This will foam up making the liquid needed.)
Blend into other ingredients and stir just to blend.
Pour batter into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with oil (or use shortening and flour method).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done in center.
Serve warm or cold.
Good with cream cheese spread. Serves 10.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake until slightly brown at 400°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown chicken breasts in light amount of oil.
Place chicken on bed of rice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and sour cream to make a sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Add remaining rice to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Time is approximate.
Check after 50 minutes.)

title: west virginia peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in heavy pan.
Combine egg yolks and milk and gradually add to dry mixture, stirring well to prevent lumps.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Cool slightly.
Then pour into baked pie shell.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and cocoa, then add salad dressing. Dissolve soda in water and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Bake in loaf pan 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pepsi cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour nuts evenly over bottom. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup crust layer. Mix together the chocolate pudding mix, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Spread this on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pudding cake
directions: Punch holes in cake and pour strawberry mixture over cake. Spread with sweetened strawberries, making a layer.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding and put on top of cake.
Chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat when mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in water.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter, vanilla and butter. Spread in buttered pan.

title: ruth's squash cheese souffle
directions: Heat milk and pour over bread crumbs. Add eggs, pepper, butter and onions, mixing well. Stir in squash and cheese. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in juice from apricots (or peaches), heated. When cooled, add buttermilk and apricots (or peaches).
Then blend in Cool Whip and extract.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: mary ann's fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix until smooth.
Add additional milk to thicken if necessary.
Batter should resemble pancake batter.
Dip tomato slices into batter, allowing excess batter to drip back into bowl.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Fry in 2 inches of hot oil in a large heavy skillet until browned, turning one carefully with tongs.
Transfer to a colander to drain.
To keep tomatoes from getting soggy before they are served, stand them up instead of stacking.

title: gary's white crumb breakfast cake
directions: Cream shortening and add flour sifted with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix into crumbs.
Take 1/2 cup of crumbs out for the top.
To remaining crumbs, add the eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat well.
Pour into two 8-inch, well-greased pans.
Put crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: picnic bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon and cut into small pieces. Add browned beef and other ingredients. Drain some of the juice from the beans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Keep covered 30 minutes of baking time.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, sugar and eggs together until creamy.
Add vanilla, soda, flour and chocolate chips and mix together.
Bake at 375°for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with taco seasoning, onion and Ro-Tel.
Drain. Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, chili beans and 1 cup of each cheese.
Reserve remainder of cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: broccoli amandine
directions: Steam
broccoli
over
rapidly boiling water until just tender.
Occasionally
I peel the stems of broccoli, reasoning that
the
flowers	and
leaves are so much the most important part
that	I
cannot
afford to overcook them for the sake of getting the stems tender.

title: camp lasagna
directions: Rub fryer pieces with Miracle Whip inside and out.
To cook outside, wrap in foil and cook on coals.
To cook at home, cook in oven at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Mix strawberries, pineapple, bananas, boiling water and jello together.
Pour half in mold.
Partially set.
Spread sour cream over gelatin.
Pour remaining jello over sour cream.
Chill until well set.

title: broccoli with mustard sauce
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk, mustard, horseradish and parsley; cook over low heat until hot and mixed well.
Serve over cooked and drained broccoli.
Serves 4.

title: apple turkey cheese sandwich
directions: Spread each slice of bread with apple cinnamon Brummel and Brown spread (approximately 2 tablespoons). Sprinkle with chopped walnuts. Layer lettuce, turkey, apples and cheese.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Pare and cut in 1/4 inch slices (peeled eggplant).
Beat egg slightly.
Add salt and pepper to flour.
Batter eggplant in flour, dip in egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry until brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening in a large skillet, brown meat, stirring occasionally to break up the large pieces. Stir in onion and cook until tender.
Pour off drippings.
Add taco sauce, enchilada sauce and beans to the meat mixture. Continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Using a greased 3-quart baking dish, place half of the tacos in bottom, cover with half of the meat mixture, half the soup and half the cheese.
Repeat the layers using the rest of the taco shells and meat, soup and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: cucumber pickles(9 day pickles)
directions: Put whole cucumbers in large mouthed jar and cover with boiling water.
Let stand overnight.
Next a.m. pour off water and cover again
with boiling water.
Repeat procedure 3 days. On day 5,	slice
cucumbers
in
1/2-inch slices.	Combine all ingredients and bring
to
a
boil;
pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
On 3rd day, bring all to a boil and pack in hot sterilized jars.
Makes approximately 3 pints.

title: jennifer's cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses soften to room temperature. Cream them together until they are thoroughly mixed. Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Roll into one or two balls or rolls. May be rolled in chopped pecans or parsley flakes. Store in refrigerator until ready to use (several hours). Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour until smooth.
Gradually add 1 cup milk, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Reduce heat and cook 3 minutes.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper, if desired.
Stir grated Velveeta cheese into white sauce.
Add 1 (4 ounce) can of green chilies which have been "chopped" in blender. Serve with Doritos.

title: strawberry flapjack stack
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease bottoms of 4 (9-inch) round cake pans. Prepare cake according to package directions. Remove from oven and let cool. Place 1 cake layer on a serving plate and frost top only with frosting swirls resembling whipped butter. Add a layer of strawberries. Repeat next 2 layers. Top stack with remaining layer. Pile frosting in center and add strawberries. Drizzle warm caramel topping over the top to resemble syrup.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken.
Bone, skin and cut in chunks.
Cook large package of broccoli until crunchy and place drained broccoli into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Combine 1 can of cream of chicken soup, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon curry powder (optional).
Pour sauce over chicken.
Take 1 1/2 to 2 cups Pepperidge Farm dressing tossed with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Press topping down well over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creole corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet, reserving drippings.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
Add onion and green pepper to drippings in skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until crisp-tender.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Chop lettuce and spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: old-fashioned icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugars and beat well.
Add eggs and cream together.
Mix flour, soda and salt, beginning with less than 3 cups.
Stir into batter.
Add flour to dough until stiff enough to mold in bread pan lined with foil.
Let set in icebox at least overnight.

title: san francisco crab melt
directions: Heat broiler.
Shred or coarsely chop crabmeat.
In medium bowl, stir together crabmeat and all remaining ingredients except bread.
Place bread slices on large cookie sheet.
Broil 5 to 6-inches from heat until toasted (1 to 2 minutes).
Turn bread slices over.
Spread each with about 1 tablespoon crabmeat mixture. Broil 5 to 6-inches from heat until cheese is bubbly (2 to 3 minutes).
Serve immediately.
Yields 20 appetizers.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll out dough until dough is 2 inches thick and as round as possible.
Mix eggs and grated cheese in small mixing bowl. Spread evenly onto rolled dough.
Evenly spread pepperoni over all the dough and then evenly spread the Mozzarella cheese over dough. Salt and pepper generously.
Roll dough tight from one end to the other.
Tuck in sides and shape into horseshoe.
Put on cooking sheet and spread egg yolk evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; let cool, then slice.

title: lola's squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook rice.
Add squash, egg, soup, bread and flour; mix well.
Add rice, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 30 minutes.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Put bread in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over bread. Beat eggs well and pour over bread and soup.
Stir in turkey. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: nacho macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 9 minutes, omitting salt and oil. Drain and return macaroni to pan. Add cheese and taco seasoning, stirring until cheese melts. Stir in salsa. Sprinkle with green onions if desired.

title: whitefish amandine(microwave method)
directions: *Fish fillets or steaks, thawed if necessary.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix water and soup. Pour rice in foil lined dish.
Add 1/2 of soup mixture.
Lay chicken on top.
Cover with remaining soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 350°.

title: meat ball cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake in 325° oven about 40 minutes or until lightly brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together. Pour in greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peggy's potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and onion in pan or Dutch oven.
Add chicken broth and enough water to just cover potatoes.
Simmer about 20 minutes until tender.
Add evaporated milk, boiled eggs and parsley flakes.
Cook on medium-low until warm.
Add butter; when melted, add Cheddar cheese.
May be thickened with cornstarch or flour, if desired.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Stir in flour.
Chill 1 hour.

title: kartwheels
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Mix flour, margarine, powdered sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms.
(If dough seems dry, add more milk, one teaspoon at a time.)

title: feta cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to stand at room temperature for 30 minutes to soften.
In medium mixing bowl, combine cheeses.
Beat with electric mixer
until nearly smooth.
Stir in olives, green onion, and basil.
Cover and chill in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Form mixture into a ball.
Wrap and chill in refrigerator about 4 hours until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon chicken(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut chicken breast in half.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place pieces in a shallow baking pan with skin side down.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lemon slices; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and baste with pan drippings.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes more, until chicken is tender.
Serve on platter garnished with lemon slices.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix well after each.
Sift flour and baking powder, add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven, turn heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: easter paska
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk, sugar, salt, butter and cool to lukewarm.
Save 2 tablespoons of the eggs and add the rest to the milk mixture.
Crumble yeast in water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add to mixture.
Add flour about 2 cups at a time until the dough can be handled.
Knead on floured board for 15 minutes. Place dough in greased bowl, grease top and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Knead again and let rise a second time for 45 minutes. After second rising, shape into 4 balls (for round breads) or into 4 loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise for 45 minutes. Brush with 2 tablespoons egg.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: juice punch
directions: Mix the preceding together.
Put in a large container and place in freezer.
When you get ready to serve, take out of freezer the night before.
This will thaw to a thick slush.
Just before serving, add almost a bottle of ginger ale.

title: salad dressing
directions: Dissolve mustard in vinegar.
Boil ingredients until thickened.
Store in jar. When ready to use, add cream to desired consistency.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour.
The last cup of flour work it in with hands.
Pat into cookie sheet.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
(The tops do not brown during baking.)
While hot, sprinkle with colored sugar and cut.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together. Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas, part of the flour and part of the sour cream.
Baking soda is added and dissolved and more flour and sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick. Take out and let it cool on rack.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cut pork
or
chicken in small pieces.	Stir-fry shrimp with oil,
salt,
pepper, m.s.g. and sugar.
Scramble egg with oil, salt and sugar.
Add peas and carrots.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, then oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add to zucchini mixture.
Add nuts, pineapple and raisins.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk, dry mustard and salt.
Mix well. Layer bread crumbs, sausage and cheese in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Put water and sugar in saucepan.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook about 5 minutes or until it coats the spoon.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat and add onion, salt, pepper and water.
Place small potatoes, carrots and tomatoes over or around meat.
Cook over low heat about 2 or 3 hours, until tender.
Add corn; cook about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine all five juices in a punch bowl and sweeten. Chill for at least 1 hour. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: vegetable creole
directions: Simmer celery and onions in small amount of water until tender.
Drain water and add oil.
Return to low heat and saute for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, basil, rosemary, celery flakes and pepper.
Cook slowly 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add peas and kidney beans.
Cover; cook 5 minutes longer until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: hershey's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.
A very delicious, soft and chewy cookie.

title: peachy muffins
directions: Drain peaches; cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Mix sauerkraut and remaining ingredients.

title: quick and easy pot pie
directions: Place cubed chicken in pan and brown.
In a large bowl, mix potatoes, peas and carrots, chicken gravy and browned chicken.

title: helen's crazy casserole
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix everything together in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma sue's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme, stir until smooth.
Add pecans, stir until thick.
Pour into buttered 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares, store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour pan. Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over hot water. Add remaining ingredients, stir until well blended.

title: chicken crescents(very good)
directions: Cook chicken in salt water; debone and cut in pieces.
Saute pepper, onion and mushrooms until tender.
Add to chicken mixture; blend well.
Separate rolls; place as much chicken mixture as possible on wide end of roll; roll up.
Be sure to seal the ends. Mix chicken soup, cheese and milk.
