Blend well.
Put half of soup mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Place chicken roll-ups on soup mixture.
Top with rest of soup mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa, sugars and salt.
Add milk and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture is boiling.
Add butter and vanilla.
Continue cooking until thickened somewhat and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm on plain cake or ice cream.

title: quick pickled peaches
directions: In a bowl, drain syrup from can of peach halves.
Put rest of ingredients in the peach syrup and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add fruit and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate for 1
week.
Good with baked ham and roasted lamb.

title: chow
directions: Cut up green tomatoes, onions, okra, squash and cabbage.
Add salt and let sit about 4 hours.
Bring vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar to a boil.
Add to vegetables and bring to boil again.
Put in jars and seal.
Put in hot water bath only until color changes (not too long).

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown meat, celery, onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese together with all other ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in kettle.
Add onions and green peppers; cook tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Bring to a boil.
Add rice when mixture boils again.
Cover and cook slowly over low heat, about 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir mixture occasionally.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and saute garlic.
Add chicken and brown evenly.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
To drippings in skillet, add onion and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add mustard and heavy cream, stirring until blended.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cook on low heat until heated through.
Serve over rice.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flavoring and mix well. Alternately add flour and milk, beating after each addition. Stir in coconut with spoon.
Spoon batter into a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dropped ginger cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop spoon-size drops onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in thin layers in 350° oven until done.

title: easy strawberry cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased pans. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: java tapioca parfaits
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Slowly pour mixture over egg white, mixing well.
Cover; chill.
Alternate layers of tapioca and whipped cream in 4 or 5 parfait glasses.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cut fruit and gumdrops into small pieces.
Dredge with flour. Add coconut, milk and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch tube pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 250° for one hour.

title: southern cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening with 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in walnuts; drop by heaping teaspoon onto greased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of cookies.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly brown. Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 6 dozen or more.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and serve over ice.

title: german sauerbraten with potato dumplings
directions: Prick beef roast through with fork.
Place beef in a 4 quart glass bowl.
Mix 2 cups water, vinegar, onion, cloves, peppercorn, salt and bay leave; pour over beef, cover and refrigerate, turning several times for 3 days.
Remove beef from marinade, pat dry, strain marinade, reserve it.
Heat oil in Dutch oven and cook beef in hot oil, turning occasionally about 10 minutes.
Remove beef, pour off fat.
Heat 2 cups of reserved marinade and 1/2 cup water to boiling in the same Dutch oven.
Reserve remaining marinade. Return beef to Dutch oven, and reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 2 hours.
Remove beef to a heated platter, keep warm.
Pour liquid from Dutch oven in a large measuring cup, skim off fat.
Add enough reserved marinade to make 2 1/2 cups.
Return to Dutch oven, stir in gingersnap crumbs and brown sugar.
Mix 1/3 cup water and flour, stir slowly into liquid. Heat to boiling stirring constantly for about 1 minute.
Strain gravy serve with beef slices and potato dumplings.

title: 4-h hot dog sauce
directions: Combine hamburger and onion, brown and drain, then add remaining ingredients.
Put in crock-pot on low or bake in oven on low 3 to 5 hours.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish. Remove the crusts from the bread and cube.
Beat
the eggs.
Gradually add the sugar, flour, salt and pineapple.
Pour all this into casserole dish and spread bread cubes on top. Add the butter on top and bake 1 hour at 400°. If bread gets too brown, put lid on dish while baking.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind all ingredients in food processor.
Add salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain off all juices.
Stir in cold cider vinegar.
Add spices.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pack in jars while hot and seal.

title: galipula from the old country(pronounced ga-lu-poo-la...from finland)
directions: Prepare the rice per directions on box.
Add mix, hamburger, rice and eggs in a large bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste (dash of Worcestershire or soy sauce optional).
Slice or leaf cabbage and line an oiled 8 x 11-inch baking pan with the cabbage. *

title: pea pilaf
directions: Fry chopped onion in vegetable oil.
Add cardamom while oil is still hot, then add peas.
Stir it on medium heat for about 3 minutes, then add rice and 2 cups of water.
Bring it to boil. Turn the heat down and let it cook until the rice is tender.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
When cooled, cut with a string so you have 4 layers.
Using a punch bowl, put one layer of cake into the bottom.
Cover with pudding, then strawberries, bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat each layer, ending with Cool Whip on the top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain and cool.
Cook broccoli as directed. Drain and cool. Cube Mozzarella cheese.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage, add onions and peppers.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti and pizza sauces and cook on simmer a few minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
Preheat crock-pot.
In crock-pot place in layers, sauce, noodles, pepperoni and Mozzarella until all used up.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots into 1/4-inch coins.
Cook until tender; drain. Combine all other ingredients together.
Mix well.
Combine with carrots. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Serve cold or warm. Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Make hamburger patties; roll patties in flour. Dip in egg and milk, then roll in flour again. Brown in shortening on both sides. Heat soups, water and milk, and pour over patties. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Rinse grapes; cut in half and remove seeds.
Place in bottom of glass serving bowl.
Peel and slice bananas; place over grapes. Drain peaches well; cut into small pieces.
Place on top of bananas.
Peel oranges; remove white skin.
Slice and cut into small pieces; place on top of raspberries.
Peel and slice kiwis. Garnish salad.
Pour orange juice over top of salad; sprinkle with powdered sugar (if used).
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Serve with macaroons, pound cake or vanilla wafers.

title: sour cream yeast bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small sauce pan.
Cook until melted. Cool.
Dissolve yeast in water for 5 minutes.
Stir sour cream mixture and egg into yeast.
Gradually add flour.
Knead. Then put in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Roll out as desired.
Let double and bake at 350°.
Start in cold oven. Makes one loaf.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers in blender with 1 cup of water.
Blend, then drain off water.

title: oyako donburi(rice with chicken and egg topping)
directions: Cook chicken in stock. Season with soy sauce, sugar and sake. Add mushrooms and Kamaboko.
Bring to a boil and add eggs. When eggs are well coddled, spoon mixture over hot rice in individual bowls.
Garnish with green onions and snow peas.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together 3/4 cup of flour, yeast, sweetener and hot water.
Stir in the oil, 1 1/4 cups of remaining flour and salt.
Blend the mixture until it forms a dough.
Knead the dough on a floured surface, incorporating as much of the remaining 1/4 cup flour as necessary to prevent the dough from sticking, for 5 to 10 minutes, or until it is smooth and elastic.

title: snickers pie(lighter eating - 3 points)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 8 inch dish and freeze. Serving size 1/8th of pie.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium size bowl, stir together sugar, Sweet One, margarine, eggs, Butter Buds sprinkles and vanilla.
In small bowl, stir together dry ingredients; stir into liquid ingredients just until blended.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt, vinegar and oil until sugar is dissolved. Add other ingredients. Let stand 1 hour.

title: jello fluff
directions: Mix cottage cheese.
Sprinkle pudding over it.
Add pineapple (drained and chopped).
Add 1/2 container Cool Whip and all marshmallows.
Stir together.
Gradually add rest of Cool Whip.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Boil first 8 ingredients.
When cool, add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300° or longer, if needed.
Batter will be very thick.
Can add 1 cup nuts if your doctor permits.

title: apricot slush
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water.
Add sugar to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.
During freezing, stir a few times.
When serving, put "scoopful" of slush in a glass and add 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken; cube and layer in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cook spaghetti and layer next.
Pour over 1 can heated spaghetti sauce.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: shrimp toast(makes 40 pieces)
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Flatten with rolling pin.
Chop first 3 ingredients.
Make paste of egg, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Blend with shrimp mixture.
Cut bread into fourths. Place teaspoon of shrimp mixture on each piece of bread.
Fry face down in hot oil.
Drain on paper toweling.

title: chicken in apricot sauce
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place in casserole and let stand in apple juice for 5 minutes.
Stir apricots, ginger and mustard. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then transfer to serving dish.
Spoon sauce over top and sprinkle with almonds.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add vanilla to oil mixture.
Stir apples and nuts in by hand. Bake in greased, floured tube pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Needs no icing.

title: spinach new orleans
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
While still hot, add cream cheese and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix seasoning; add lemon juice. Place in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle herb dressing on top.
Melt remaining butter and drizzle over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chinese-style spareribs
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter and cook garlic with soup.
Heat 1 minute until golden brown.
Stir in tomato puree, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and chili sauce.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally.
In aluminum foil-lined baking pan, arrange meat.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Brush ribs with sauce and cook another 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and salt; bring to a boil.
Watch it does not boil over.
Boil until it forms a small ball in cold water.
Butter pan; add peanut butter.
Stir and pour into buttered pan.
Cool, then slice into squares.

title: mississippi roasted squirrel
directions: Wash squirrels thoroughly; dry.
Cover with cooking oil mixed with lemon juice.
Let stand 1 hour.
Combine crumbs with just enough milk to moisten along with all other ingredients, except bacon fat.
Stuff the squirrels.
Place in roaster; brush on bacon fat.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours, basting about every 15 minutes with drippings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and margarine; blend well.
Add sugar and whip.
Add 1/2 milk and 1/2 flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
(Blend well after adding each egg.)
Add remainder of milk and flour.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Place in cold oven set at 300°.
Bake one hour.
Bake another 1/2 hour at 325°.
Remove from pan immediately and cover.
(Have all ingredients at room temperature before beginning to bake.)

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions. Fold in Cool Whip. Drain fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and cherries. Fold well-drained fruit into pudding mixture. Add marshmallows and bananas. Chill thoroughly. Serve in lettuce cups.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck in a frying pan and drain. Put in slow cooker, adding remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook, covered, on low 8 to 10 hours or high for 5 hours.

title: meal-in-one
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, put diced raw potatoes to cover the bottom, raw rice, browned ground beef, chopped onion and enough diced carrots to cover.
Place in order given.
Pour tomato juice over all until all is covered.
Salt each layer.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: "spa-zaunga"
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Stir in Ragu sauce.
Cook noodles until done; drain and add to sauce. Stir in Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add milk.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put layer of apples, then sprinkle in sugar and cinnamon. Mix together.
Repeat until all is used.
Sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs, then melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into patties.
Brown on both sides for 5 minutes on each side.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean; cool before serving. Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and Cheddar cheese into a soft dough. Beat dough vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by soup spoon size spoon fulls onto ungreased cookie sheet. For smaller biscuits, use a
teaspoon. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown at 450°. While biscuits are baking, add garlic powder to melted margarine. Brush garlic margarine over hot biscuits when they come out of the oven.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Add broccoli and onion.
Warm through and serve in chafing dish or pan that can be kept warm with assorted crackers.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with pimento, green pepper and onions.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil, remove from heat and cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift all dry ingredients in a small bowl, then take turns adding the sifted dry ingredients and the milk to the fluffy egg mixture until they have all been added.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pan (10 x 15 x 1-inch) and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Save 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Cut carrots lengthwise.
Combine 1/4 cup cooking liquid with mayo, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with oleo, paprika and parsley.
Cook uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: blair's broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli and butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave (High) for 2 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Stir in milk and next 6 ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave at Medium-high (70%) for 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in wine.
Cover tightly and microwave on Medium-high for 5 to 6 minutes or until thickened, stirring every 2 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Spoon over 2 to 3 pounds chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in colander.
Cover with ice and drain for 3 hours.
Place in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Jar and seal.

title: your choice fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: easy coconut custard pie(makes its own crust!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass pie dish).
Combine first 6 ingredients in blender or processor.
Blend on low speed 3 minutes.
If your blender won't hold it all, put in as much milk as it will hold.
Blend, then stir in remaining milk.
Pour into buttered pie dish and let rest 5 minutes, then sprinkle coconut on top and bake 30 to 40 minutes for 9-inch pies or 35 to 45 minutes for a 10-inch pie or until set.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 1 (10-inch) pie.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine beans, 3 tablespoons tomato sauce and 1 teaspoon Tabasco sauce.
Spread in bottom of 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Top with tomatoes and Monterey Jack cheese.
Brown the ground beef; drain.
Stir in chili powder, the rest of Tabasco sauce, tomato sauce, olives, salt and peppers.
Spread on top of cheese. Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with peaches.
Melt butter in pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter in pan on the butter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: summer chicken with peas
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add chicken and potatoes and brown
slowly
on
all
sides;
salt and pepper.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice; reduce heat, cover pan and simmer 30 minutes. Add
onions to butter in bottom of skillet; sprinkle peas and parsley
over chicken and potatoes; cover and simmer 10 minutes more
or
until
chicken
and
potatoes
are done. Remove chicken and
vegetables to serving platter; keep warm. Remove skillet from heat.
Add sour cream, thyme, 1/2 teaspoon salt and
teaspoon pepper.
Stir
to	mix
well with pan drippings.
Pour over chicken or serve as a sauce.

title: hot dog chili
directions: In large frypan, mix hamburger and sausage and fry until done. Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and tomato soup to meat.
Add chili powder to taste.
Cook on low for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: linda's easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Let rolls rise in a 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam (don't cover).
Melt margarine and mix with cinnamon sugar.
Pour mixture between rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Frost with mixture of powdered sugar and milk.
May also decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: chuck roast
directions: Tear 2 long pieces of aluminum foil and place crisscross on table.
Place meat on foil and put 2 tablespoons steak sauce over meat.
Put dry onion soup over meat.
Put mushroom soup from can over meat.
Wrap foil around meat so liquid cannot run out.
Cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
If desired, you can add potatoes and carrots to meat.
Meat will have its own gravy.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey burger
directions: Mix the ground turkey and salsa thoroughly.
Fry and put on bun with your favorite trimmings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 3 crumb crust pie shells and chill for 1 hour.

title: nellie (ma) summer's red beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cover good with water to cook.
After beans begin to cook, add ginger.
Cook for 1 hour before adding other ingredients.
Add small amounts of water as necessary.
Cook approximately 6 to 8 hours.
Feeds about 100 people.
Good for church dinners, etc.

title: saucy peas and zucchini
directions: Place unopened pea pouch in vigorously boiling water in saucepan; do not cover.
Bring to a boil; boil rapidly for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, simmer zucchini in 2 tablespoons water until water is reduced and zucchini is tender.
Stir in pimiento and peas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible crab quiche
directions: Blend Bisquick, butter, milk, eggs, salt and pepper. Blend well. Pour into pan. Sprinkle crabmeat on top and push it down. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: party ice cream flowerpots
directions: You will need 12 flowerpots, 12 straws and 12 daisies or other longer stem flower.

title: cheese dip
directions: Lay cheese out of refrigerator so it will be soft.
Thin cheese to dip consistency with a little cream or milk.
Add all other ingredients; mix well and store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Break up corned beef and combine with cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Mix well. Place in baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and flavorings.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool about 15 minutes in pan. (I like to add some cinnamon, ginger or allspice.
Choose one you like!)

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add baking powder, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Fold in nuts, raisins and carrots.
Bake 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a kettle and boil on medium heat for exactly 3 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into a buttered pan (9 x 12-inch) and let cool.

title: old fashioned macaroni salad
directions: Drop
macaroni
into
rapidly boiling water, boil until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Chill in refrigerator. Mix remaining ingredients with macaroni.
Mix mayonnaise and French
dressing;
pour
over macaroni, then toss lightly until thoroughly
mixed.
Chill again in refrigerator.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla, butter and nuts. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 25 minutes longer.

title: greek omelet for two
directions: In medium saucepan, cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
In same pan, combine spinach, cheeses, onion, mint and pepper.
Heat through over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: coconut-cornflake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease baking sheets; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat to combine.
Gradually add sugar, beating until egg whites are stiff.
Beat in extract.
Gently fold in cornflakes and coconut.

title: holiday squash
directions: Mix and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 370°.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve with raw vegetables (carrots, cauliflower, radishes, celery, cucumbers, broccoli and cherry tomatoes).
This will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks or longer.

title: stuffed rock cornish hens burgundy
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and stuff hens. Lightly salt and pepper hens.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Let bubble until thick.
Place hens in a roasting pan and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting often with glaze.
Split hens down the middle to serve. Pass remaining sauce.
Excellent.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy cauliflower italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
In a greased 8-inch square casserole, layer 1/2 of each of the following ingredients in order:

cauliflower, onion, flour mixture, butter pieces, olive, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Repeat layering with second 1/2 of ingredients, adding parsley flakes between olive slices and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Combine wine and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven 40 to 45 minutes or until golden and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and 1 egg at a time (rotating flour and eggs).
Add flavoring last. Cook 1 hour at 325°.
If the cake seems to be cooking too fast, turn down to 300°.

title: macaroni-oyster casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water.
In casserole dish, place layer of macaroni, layer of oysters, small amount of pepper, salt and butter.
Repeat layers.
Add all juice from oysters and 1 cup of milk to casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot smothered steak
directions: Divide onion rings into three portions:
place one portion in bottom of crock-pot.

title: debbie's black bean chili
directions: Place beans in at least as much water to cover by 2 inches. Let soak a minimum of 8 hours; check occasionally to ensure that water covers the beans, adding additional water when necessary. Pick over tomatoes, separating any that are bruised.
Cut out damaged portions.
Slip tomatoes into boiling water for about 3 minutes, or just long enough so that the skin begins to crack. Transfer by a slotted spoon into a container of ice water.
Let cool until cool enough to handle; slip off skins and place into a container to be dumped into your compost bin.
Cut larger tomatoes into quarters and place into your food processor.
Process until no large chunks of tomatoes remain; repeat with remaining tomatoes.
Reserve this tomato puree until beans are ready.

title: mystery hot dish
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with raw hamburger.
Place croutons over this.
Heat other ingredients together and pour over top. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Let stand for 15 minutes. Cut and serve.
Can be frozen also.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Add barbecue sauce on top chicken. Bake until done.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until set.

title: pineapple mouse
directions: Mix pineapple, marshmallows, and cheese & let set overnight or several hours then add: whipping cream (whipped) and let set in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: texas brownies
directions: In large bowl combine flour and sugar.
In heavy saucepan combine butter, shortening, coffee and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using a wooden spoon.
Pour into a well-buttered 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Pepper pork chops and sprinkle heavily with Worcestershire sauce.
Heat oven to 325°.
Put rice in pan.
Heat water and bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Add broth to pan with rice.
Heat skillet until very hot.
(Cast iron skillet is best.)
Add 2 pork chops at a time in skillet and brown (don't cook), 30 seconds on each side.
Add to rice, cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Open and drain all fruit.
Save the juice.
Use 6 cups of juice to cook pudding and tapioca.
If not enough juice, add water to make 6 cups.
Cook pudding; cool, then add fruit.
Store in fridge.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown
beef and onion together, adding salt and pepper, if desired.
In
a 2 quart casserole, spread half of the beef mixture.
Add
a
layer
of
shredded cabbage.
Repeat layers. Spread
a can of tomato soup over top.
Bake at 350°, covered, until
cabbage
is
tender and soup is hot and mixed with beef and cabbage.

title: buckskin bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients, then quickly mix in the water.
Press the dough into a 9-inch pie pan and bake in a hot oven at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in unbaked crust.
Cook at 350° until crust is brown, about 30 minutes.
So easy.

title: stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry vegetables in a little oil.
Remove.
Cut pork chops or steak in strips and stir-fry.
Remove meat and mix with vegetables.
Put over 1 medium package cooked buttered noodles. Pour chicken broth in pan where meat was stir-fried and bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with salt and water and pour into boiling broth.
Add Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Pour over stir-fry mixture.

title: baked green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, blend soup, milk and pepper. Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 more minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup to sprinkle over batter.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sour cream and eggs; mix well.
Pour into wax paper-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chopped nuts and cinnamon may be sprinkled over crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: triscuit pizza snacks
directions: Place Triscuits on a microwavable plate.
Cut Mozzarella cheese to fit on Triscuits.
Then place a pepperoni slice on top of cheese.
Place in microwave for about 1 minute until cheese has melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Rice should be mostly split when done, about 1 hour & 15 minutes. Saute onion in margarine, add flour and stir; stir into drained rice. Add broth gradually, then remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, simmer 5 minutes. If chilled or frozen to store, thin with milk when rewarming.

title: graham-streusel coffee cake
directions: For Streusel:
Combine graham cracker crumbs, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in melted butter; set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage get to room temperature.
Mix all 3 ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: sausage sandwich
directions: In large saucepan, melt 1 cup butter.
Add vegetables.
When they start to cook, add sausage.
Turn down heat, cover and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In another saucepan, melt the other cup of butter.
Slice buns in half.
Put bun in butter for about 1 minute.
Do the same with the other buns. After finished, place a piece of sausage and some vegetables on the bun.

title: mother johnson's irish cream
directions: In a large bottle, combine condensed milk, half and half, whiskey, instant coffee and liqueur.
Mix well and chill before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: texas taco soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat. Add corn, pinto beans and Ranch beans (do not drain). Blend Ro-Tel tomatoes and regular tomatoes in blender (do not drain). Add to corn and beans. Add meat mixture. Stir in Ranch dressing mix and taco mix. Simmer over low heat 15 to 30 minutes. Serve with Fritos, green onions or just grilled cheese.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well, then add milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Makes 3 layers or 1 pan regular cake pan.
Bake at 350°.
This cake has more flavor if baked 1 day before eating.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, coconut, pecans, oleo and vanilla.
Form into balls; chill overnight.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate.
Put on waxed paper to dry.
Makes 100.

title: sausage balls
directions: Squish together with hands.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine ingredients and store.
Mix with hot water.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour mixture into pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Mix sour cream and dry dip.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: salisbury steak bake
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties; place in shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Mix rest of soup and 1/3 cup water; pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watkins' economy cake
directions: Boil sugar, water, lard and raisins together for 3 minutes until sugar is dissolved; cool mix.
Sift together all dry ingredients and stir into cooled raisin mixture.
Add vanilla. Pour into square cake pan and bake about 25 minutes at 350°. Serve plain or with white frosting.

title: low-fat harvest soup
directions: Brown the turkey and add all of the ingredients.
Cook until done.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: perfect meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients thoroughly with 1 can tomato sauce. Pack firmly into an 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill about 1 hour. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over meat loaf and continue baking 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, pepper, onions and celery in bowl.
In another bowl, mix sour cream, soup and cheese.
Combine soup and vegetables.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with crackers, butter and almonds.
Bake in oven 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in a large saucepan. Stir in milk slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, over moderate heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture is very thick, about 6 minutes longer. Beat eggs in medium size bowl until frothy.
Stir 1/2 of cooked mixture; blend well.
Return to saucepan, blending in mixture. Cook 2 minutes more over low heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Place a piece of plastic wrap directly on surface; cool.
Slice bananas into pie shell.
Pour cooled cream filling over bananas.
Chill.

title: san francisco stir-fry
directions: *Fresh veggies are very good.

title: sin cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour water over oats and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, dry ingredients and 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Mix rest of chips and nuts; sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill until ready to serve.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
(Beat about 17 minutes.)
Add eggs, beating one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients.
Alternate adding flour and whipping cream to sugar and shortening.
Mix slowly.
Place in a greased and floured tube pan or 16 1/2 x 4-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 275°, then move temperature up to 325° for 30 minutes without opening oven door, or moving pan.
Test for doneness by toothpick.
Do not overcook. Cake should be moist.

title: egg bake
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef with onion until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain.
Butter bottom and sides of 9 x 13 pan.
Line the bottom with 8 slices of bread.
Layer meat and cheese mixture, beginning with meat, ending with cheese, until all are used up.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over layers in baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: sloppy lentils(swimmer's delight)
directions: Place lentils, onion,
carrot
and
green pepper into a large pot with 4 cups water.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add tomato sauce and
seasonings
to
the
pot.
Simmer for 30 more minutes.
Serve over rice (yellow).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar chicken divan
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and seasoning. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Arrange broccoli/asparagus and chicken in 11 1/2 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken breasts and peppers
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add teriyaki sauce, mushrooms and onion in large frypan.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer.
Add chicken (do not overcook).
Cook on one side until slightly pink on top.
Add peppers and turn chicken.
Cook until peppers are tender-crisp (4 minutes). Thicken with cornstarch mixed in a little water.
Add sherry and cook one more minute.
Serve over rice or put into casserole and top with tomato slices, slightly heated.

title: chinese lemon chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken) in small saucepan and cook until thickened and clear.
Pour over raw chicken and bake at 400° for about 1 hour, uncovered. Spray Pam on casserole dish.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift cocoa, cake flour and 3/4 cup sugar together 4 times. Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Sprinkle cream of tartar over egg whites; continue beating until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in remaining sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Fold in dry ingredients, a little at a time. Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.
Frost, if desired, although it is delicious plain.

title: oyster stew
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove and place on paper towel.
Discard excess grease.
Dice celery and onion.
Saute in remaining grease until tender.
Add oysters and liquor in pan and heat until oysters curl.
Have milk heated and when oysters have curled, stir oyster mixture into milk.
Add Old Bay seasoning.
Add butter. Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top of stew after it has been dished into plates.

title: baked alaska pie
directions: Combine coconut and butter.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Melt marshmallows and chocolate in milk over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Pack ice cream into crust; cover with chocolate sauce.
Freeze until firm.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat until meringue will stand in peaks.
Spread over filling, sealing to crust.
Sprinkle with additional coconut.
Place pie on board.
Bake at 500° for about 2 minutes, or until brown.
Serve immediately or return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: snicker cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and milk.
Press 1/2 of this into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (slightly greased).
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle on nuts and chocolate chips.
Melt together caramels and evaporated milk.
Pour over the chocolate mixture.
Spread the rest of cake mix batter over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs; beat well. Alternately add milk, flour and baking soda (mixed together); mix well and add chocolate mixture last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch layer pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Larger pan, bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Press crescent rolls in bottom of pie plate.
Crush nacho Doritos and sprinkle on top of rolls.
Brown hamburger and drain. Add taco seasoning and a little bit of water.
Pour over chips. Spread sour cream over meat.
Cover with cheese.
Crush up remaining Doritos.
Bake at 350° until brown (10 to 15 minutes).

title: carolina red rice
directions: Fry the bacon in a large pot or Dutch oven until crisp.

Add oil and saute onion, celery and bell peppers until tender. To this, add the tomatoes with the liquid and 2 cups water. Cook at a rolling boil for 20 minutes. Add rice to the pot and stir well. When mixture returns to a boil, reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 30 minutes or until rice is fluffy. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese-sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage.
Combine soup, relish and garlic powder with sausage, then add cheese until melted.

title: chicken in sweet milk gravy
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; roll in corn meal and brown in a skillet.
Remove from skillet and pour off excess grease.
Leave enough to make gravy.
Add 1/4 cup meal, salt and pepper to grease.
Brown.
Add 2 1/2 cups sweet milk.
Put chicken back in gravy and simmer about 15 minutes.
